WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.473 align:middle line:90%
[WHOOSH]

00:00:01.473 --> 00:00:04.910 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.910 --> 00:00:08.347 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:08.347 --> 00:00:09.329 align:middle line:90%


00:00:09.329 --> 00:00:14.730 align:middle line:90%
[BACKGROUND MUSIC]

00:00:14.730 --> 00:00:24.348 align:middle line:90%


00:00:24.348 --> 00:00:26.390 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Well,
welcome to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:26.390 --> 00:00:29.090 align:middle line:10%
Our very special guest,
Richard Estep is with us.

00:00:29.090 --> 00:00:31.460 align:middle line:10%
Now Richard is
paranormal author who

00:00:31.460 --> 00:00:34.820 align:middle line:10%
has written more than a dozen
books detailing its most

00:00:34.820 --> 00:00:37.070 align:middle line:10%
harrowing investigations.

00:00:37.070 --> 00:00:40.340 align:middle line:84%
Richard has also co-founded
the Boulder County Paranormal

00:00:40.340 --> 00:00:45.350 align:middle line:84%
Research Group with his wife,
Laura, and that was in 1999.

00:00:45.350 --> 00:00:48.380 align:middle line:84%
And he has also appeared on
a number of television shows,

00:00:48.380 --> 00:00:51.390 align:middle line:84%
"Haunted Hospitals" and
"Paranormal 911" on the Travel

00:00:51.390 --> 00:00:52.190 align:middle line:90%
Channel.

00:00:52.190 --> 00:00:53.780 align:middle line:84%
Richard, welcome
to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:53.780 --> 00:00:54.920 align:middle line:84%
>>RICHARD ESTEP: Thank
you for having me, George.

00:00:54.920 --> 00:00:57.112 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How did you get
involved in all of this?

00:00:57.112 --> 00:00:59.570 align:middle line:10%
>>ESTEP: Well, as a young kid,
I grew up in a haunted house

00:00:59.570 --> 00:01:00.695 align:middle line:10%
that my grandparents owned.

00:01:00.695 --> 00:01:01.520 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Ooh.

00:01:01.520 --> 00:01:03.270 align:middle line:10%
>>ESTEP: And that
fascinated me, you know?

00:01:03.270 --> 00:01:05.220 align:middle line:10%
There were no TV shows
back in those days.

00:01:05.220 --> 00:01:07.340 align:middle line:10%
There were no "Ghost
Hunters," "Ghost Adventures"

00:01:07.340 --> 00:01:07.880 align:middle line:10%
kind of shows.

00:01:07.880 --> 00:01:09.140 align:middle line:10%
And you had to go to books.

00:01:09.140 --> 00:01:11.720 align:middle line:10%
You had to haunt your library,
if you'll pardon the pun,

00:01:11.720 --> 00:01:13.290 align:middle line:10%
in order to get your ghost fix.

00:01:13.290 --> 00:01:14.797 align:middle line:90%
And I was that kid.

00:01:14.797 --> 00:01:16.880 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And it stuck with
you forever, didn't it?

00:01:16.880 --> 00:01:17.680 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Forever.

00:01:17.680 --> 00:01:20.150 align:middle line:84%
And came with me when I moved
from the US-- excuse me,

00:01:20.150 --> 00:01:22.305 align:middle line:90%
the UK to the US in 1999.

00:01:22.305 --> 00:01:23.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What caused
that move for you?

00:01:23.930 --> 00:01:27.080 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: I worked for a
local company here, IBM,

00:01:27.080 --> 00:01:28.167 align:middle line:90%
in Boulder, Colorado.

00:01:28.167 --> 00:01:29.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Just a
small, little company.

00:01:29.750 --> 00:01:31.190 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Yeah, a
small, little company.

00:01:31.190 --> 00:01:33.380 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And you never forgot
the paranormal, did you?

00:01:33.380 --> 00:01:35.880 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: You know, it got into
my blood at a very young age.

00:01:35.880 --> 00:01:38.990 align:middle line:84%
And all kids love ghost stories,
but I never outgrew that love.

00:01:38.990 --> 00:01:42.800 align:middle line:84%
And I spent years in the UK
investigating and learning

00:01:42.800 --> 00:01:45.140 align:middle line:84%
the technique for researching
claims of the paranormal.

00:01:45.140 --> 00:01:47.120 align:middle line:84%
And there were so
many great places here

00:01:47.120 --> 00:01:49.610 align:middle line:84%
in the United States
to bring that to.

00:01:49.610 --> 00:01:52.272 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is it that
makes a house haunted?

00:01:52.272 --> 00:01:54.230 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Oh, that's a
great question, isn't it?

00:01:54.230 --> 00:01:56.150 align:middle line:84%
Generally speaking, in
my experience, George,

00:01:56.150 --> 00:01:57.920 align:middle line:84%
there are three
types of haunting.

00:01:57.920 --> 00:02:00.590 align:middle line:84%
You've got haunted
places, haunted objects,

00:02:00.590 --> 00:02:01.890 align:middle line:90%
and haunted people.

00:02:01.890 --> 00:02:03.890 align:middle line:84%
So it might be somebody
that lives in the house.

00:02:03.890 --> 00:02:06.890 align:middle line:84%
It might be the house itself, or
the ground that it's built on.

00:02:06.890 --> 00:02:07.860 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Or the ground.

00:02:07.860 --> 00:02:08.660 align:middle line:90%
That's good.

00:02:08.660 --> 00:02:09.919 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Or an
object that has been

00:02:09.919 --> 00:02:11.630 align:middle line:84%
brought into the
house, and sometimes

00:02:11.630 --> 00:02:13.100 align:middle line:90%
a combination of all three.

00:02:13.100 --> 00:02:15.740 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Would you ever want
to live atop a cemetery?

00:02:15.740 --> 00:02:18.020 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: You know, isn't
America one big cemetery?

00:02:18.020 --> 00:02:21.065 align:middle line:84%
Isn't every country one
big cemetery, essentially?

00:02:21.065 --> 00:02:22.940 align:middle line:84%
Having come from the
London area in the past,

00:02:22.940 --> 00:02:26.000 align:middle line:84%
London is built upon
generations of Londoners.

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:28.740 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's built on
plague pits dating back

00:02:28.740 --> 00:02:29.540 align:middle line:90%
to the Black Death.

00:02:29.540 --> 00:02:31.580 align:middle line:84%
So in a kind of
real sense, we all

00:02:31.580 --> 00:02:32.930 align:middle line:90%
do live on top of a cemetery.

00:02:32.930 --> 00:02:33.888 align:middle line:90%
That's what society is.

00:02:33.888 --> 00:02:36.013 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Would you like to
live in a haunted house,

00:02:36.013 --> 00:02:37.430 align:middle line:90%
knowing somebody died there?

00:02:37.430 --> 00:02:38.600 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: I mean, I have.

00:02:38.600 --> 00:02:41.690 align:middle line:84%
I've spent time living in
several haunted locations,

00:02:41.690 --> 00:02:45.320 align:middle line:84%
and one of them at least
belonged to a serial killer.

00:02:45.320 --> 00:02:47.010 align:middle line:84%
The murders took
place in the house.

00:02:47.010 --> 00:02:47.810 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:02:47.810 --> 00:02:49.970 align:middle line:84%
That was Fox Hollow
Farm in Indiana.

00:02:49.970 --> 00:02:51.105 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh my god.

00:02:51.105 --> 00:02:53.480 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And it's not always
the most pleasant of things,

00:02:53.480 --> 00:02:55.760 align:middle line:84%
but yeah, I'm OK with
that kind of background.

00:02:55.760 --> 00:02:58.520 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I don't think I'd want
to live in a house like that.

00:02:58.520 --> 00:02:59.550 align:middle line:90%
Too much energy.

00:02:59.550 --> 00:03:00.645 align:middle line:90%
Negative energy there.

00:03:00.645 --> 00:03:02.270 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: But you
know, there are people

00:03:02.270 --> 00:03:04.830 align:middle line:84%
that bring positive energies
to places like that.

00:03:04.830 --> 00:03:06.350 align:middle line:90%
And I like the idea.

00:03:06.350 --> 00:03:08.420 align:middle line:84%
Energy, after all, is
what this is all about.

00:03:08.420 --> 00:03:10.640 align:middle line:84%
I like the idea that you
can convert a negative

00:03:10.640 --> 00:03:11.990 align:middle line:90%
into a positive.

00:03:11.990 --> 00:03:15.020 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When you go to
these haunted locations,

00:03:15.020 --> 00:03:18.590 align:middle line:84%
are people calling you, saying,
hey, this house may be haunted,

00:03:18.590 --> 00:03:20.000 align:middle line:90%
come investigate it?

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:21.333 align:middle line:90%
Or do you already know about it?

00:03:21.333 --> 00:03:23.667 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Well, much like
yourself, George, I'm a writer,

00:03:23.667 --> 00:03:25.310 align:middle line:84%
and I'm always
interested in a story.

00:03:25.310 --> 00:03:26.580 align:middle line:90%
A human story.

00:03:26.580 --> 00:03:27.380 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:03:27.380 --> 00:03:28.928 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And so I
generally will be

00:03:28.928 --> 00:03:30.470 align:middle line:84%
interested in the
lives of those that

00:03:30.470 --> 00:03:34.190 align:middle line:84%
have lived at the location and
the strange things that occur

00:03:34.190 --> 00:03:35.670 align:middle line:90%
while people are living there.

00:03:35.670 --> 00:03:37.070 align:middle line:90%
So that's what I always look at.

00:03:37.070 --> 00:03:38.960 align:middle line:84%
What's the story
to be told here,

00:03:38.960 --> 00:03:41.230 align:middle line:84%
and how can I add a
chapter of my own?

00:03:41.230 --> 00:03:43.030 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's amazing
work that you do.

00:03:43.030 --> 00:03:43.940 align:middle line:90%
You like it.

00:03:43.940 --> 00:03:44.360 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: I love it.

00:03:44.360 --> 00:03:45.160 align:middle line:90%
It's my passion.

00:03:45.160 --> 00:03:47.930 align:middle line:84%
Most people go on vacation
and they'll take a cruise

00:03:47.930 --> 00:03:50.232 align:middle line:84%
or go sit on the
beach, you know?

00:03:50.232 --> 00:03:52.190 align:middle line:84%
I'm fortunate I have an
understanding wife that

00:03:52.190 --> 00:03:54.080 align:middle line:84%
lets me go live in
an old abandoned

00:03:54.080 --> 00:03:56.730 align:middle line:90%
hospital for a week or a jail.

00:03:56.730 --> 00:03:57.530 align:middle line:90%
I go to jail--

00:03:57.530 --> 00:04:00.408 align:middle line:84%
I've done a lot of jail time
as a paranormal investigator.

00:04:00.408 --> 00:04:01.700 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Are jails haunted too?

00:04:01.700 --> 00:04:02.533 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Enormously.

00:04:02.533 --> 00:04:04.040 align:middle line:84%
When you think
about it, the amount

00:04:04.040 --> 00:04:05.623 align:middle line:84%
of negative energy
you get in a jail--

00:04:05.623 --> 00:04:06.582 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, it's huge.

00:04:06.582 --> 00:04:08.910 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: --the amount of
despair, the amount of anger,

00:04:08.910 --> 00:04:10.550 align:middle line:90%
the amount of hatred.

00:04:10.550 --> 00:04:13.010 align:middle line:84%
It would amaze me if
some kind of psychic scar

00:04:13.010 --> 00:04:14.660 align:middle line:90%
wasn't left over from that.

00:04:14.660 --> 00:04:16.505 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What drives you, Rich?

00:04:16.505 --> 00:04:19.178 align:middle line:90%
What pushes you into this area?

00:04:19.178 --> 00:04:20.720 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: I think
like everybody else,

00:04:20.720 --> 00:04:22.490 align:middle line:84%
I've always had this
fascination of what

00:04:22.490 --> 00:04:24.560 align:middle line:90%
happens to us after we die.

00:04:24.560 --> 00:04:27.200 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we all want to know,
and we'll all find out one day.

00:04:27.200 --> 00:04:28.075 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Or we won't.

00:04:28.075 --> 00:04:28.950 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Or we won't.

00:04:28.950 --> 00:04:30.140 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] Yeah, absolutely.

00:04:30.140 --> 00:04:31.080 align:middle line:90%
Good point.

00:04:31.080 --> 00:04:32.810 align:middle line:90%
But to that, I want to--

00:04:32.810 --> 00:04:35.510 align:middle line:84%
I've always wanted to have
a look behind the veil

00:04:35.510 --> 00:04:36.890 align:middle line:90%
to see what's in the next room.

00:04:36.890 --> 00:04:38.750 align:middle line:84%
It's that curiosity
that drives me.

00:04:38.750 --> 00:04:41.100 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We've got an
investigator, Jeff Belanger,

00:04:41.100 --> 00:04:43.610 align:middle line:84%
a great guy who's talked
about traveling to a haunted

00:04:43.610 --> 00:04:44.030 align:middle line:90%
location.

00:04:44.030 --> 00:04:45.860 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And a master
storyteller too, is Jeff.

00:04:45.860 --> 00:04:47.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Let's look
at one of his stories.

00:04:47.610 --> 00:04:49.492 align:middle line:90%


00:04:49.492 --> 00:04:50.950 align:middle line:10%
>>JEFF BELANGER:
If you want to say

00:04:50.950 --> 00:04:53.010 align:middle line:10%
there's no such thing
as ghosts, that's fine.

00:04:53.010 --> 00:04:54.480 align:middle line:10%
I don't personally believe that.

00:04:54.480 --> 00:04:56.880 align:middle line:10%
But at the same time,
the stories are real.

00:04:56.880 --> 00:04:58.080 align:middle line:10%
The history's real.

00:04:58.080 --> 00:04:59.850 align:middle line:10%
And in a lot of
respects, George,

00:04:59.850 --> 00:05:02.190 align:middle line:10%
ghosts are history
demanding to be remembered.

00:05:02.190 --> 00:05:04.110 align:middle line:10%
To talk about ghosts,
to talk about hauntings

00:05:04.110 --> 00:05:06.540 align:middle line:10%
is to talk about our past,
to connect with our past,

00:05:06.540 --> 00:05:08.700 align:middle line:10%
with our ancestors,
with our history.

00:05:08.700 --> 00:05:11.315 align:middle line:10%
All of that stuff goes into
making us who we are today.

00:05:11.315 --> 00:05:12.690 align:middle line:10%
And what better
way to explore it

00:05:12.690 --> 00:05:13.940 align:middle line:10%
than with these great stories?

00:05:13.940 --> 00:05:15.855 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: You have a
passion for this stuff.

00:05:15.855 --> 00:05:17.105 align:middle line:10%
>>BELANGER: I love this stuff.

00:05:17.105 --> 00:05:18.190 align:middle line:10%
It's so much fun.

00:05:18.190 --> 00:05:20.910 align:middle line:10%
You know, when I travel, I
want to see haunted places.

00:05:20.910 --> 00:05:22.950 align:middle line:10%
I want to become part
of those stories.

00:05:22.950 --> 00:05:24.810 align:middle line:10%
You know, you hear these things,
you see them on television,

00:05:24.810 --> 00:05:26.310 align:middle line:10%
you hear them on
"Coast to Coast,"

00:05:26.310 --> 00:05:29.190 align:middle line:10%
and you want to see them for
yourselves, because maybe,

00:05:29.190 --> 00:05:31.320 align:middle line:10%
just maybe you're going
to have that experience,

00:05:31.320 --> 00:05:35.010 align:middle line:10%
that once-in-a-lifetime event
that makes you say, whoa.

00:05:35.010 --> 00:05:36.750 align:middle line:10%
There's more to this
than meets the eye.

00:05:36.750 --> 00:05:38.670 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Why are these
places, Jeff, haunted?

00:05:38.670 --> 00:05:42.510 align:middle line:10%
I mean, what is creating
this kind of energy

00:05:42.510 --> 00:05:45.630 align:middle line:10%
where these spirits,
entities, whatever they may be

00:05:45.630 --> 00:05:46.650 align:middle line:10%
hang around?

00:05:46.650 --> 00:05:48.608 align:middle line:10%
>>BELANGER: That's the
million dollar question.

00:05:48.608 --> 00:05:50.550 align:middle line:10%
[LAUGHS] If I knew
for sure, I think

00:05:50.550 --> 00:05:53.310 align:middle line:10%
there's as many reasons for
ghosts as there are ghosts.

00:05:53.310 --> 00:05:56.010 align:middle line:10%
In some respects, there's
a tragedy that took place.

00:05:56.010 --> 00:05:57.790 align:middle line:10%
And people talk
about that tragedy.

00:05:57.790 --> 00:05:58.590 align:middle line:10%
We relive it.

00:05:58.590 --> 00:06:00.420 align:middle line:10%
We give energy to it the
more we say, oh, this

00:06:00.420 --> 00:06:02.100 align:middle line:10%
is where there was a
murder or a suicide

00:06:02.100 --> 00:06:03.720 align:middle line:10%
or an unfortunate death.

00:06:03.720 --> 00:06:06.790 align:middle line:10%
And so that's often the
backstory of a haunting.

00:06:06.790 --> 00:06:07.590 align:middle line:10%
But not always.

00:06:07.590 --> 00:06:09.132 align:middle line:10%
Sometimes it's just
like a movie that

00:06:09.132 --> 00:06:10.570 align:middle line:10%
replays over and over again.

00:06:10.570 --> 00:06:12.210 align:middle line:10%
It's just the past
that just almost

00:06:12.210 --> 00:06:13.605 align:middle line:10%
gets imprinted on a location.

00:06:13.605 --> 00:06:15.870 align:middle line:10%
We might call it the
stone tape theory.

00:06:15.870 --> 00:06:19.590 align:middle line:10%
But there's so many different
theories to what's the reasons.

00:06:19.590 --> 00:06:23.670 align:middle line:10%
To me, it's simply a place
is haunted when people

00:06:23.670 --> 00:06:25.770 align:middle line:10%
have experiences, when
they talk about it,

00:06:25.770 --> 00:06:27.240 align:middle line:10%
and it gets a reputation.

00:06:27.240 --> 00:06:30.000 align:middle line:10%
Now, if things happen often,
it's an active haunting.

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:31.932 align:middle line:10%
If it's years in
between, not so much.

00:06:31.932 --> 00:06:32.890 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He's like you.

00:06:32.890 --> 00:06:35.220 align:middle line:90%
He's excited about what he does.

00:06:35.220 --> 00:06:37.590 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And Jeff makes some
very salient points there,

00:06:37.590 --> 00:06:40.900 align:middle line:84%
and he talked about some of the
things like murder and suicide.

00:06:40.900 --> 00:06:44.280 align:middle line:84%
But I would also add that
positive hauntings occur

00:06:44.280 --> 00:06:47.640 align:middle line:84%
very commonly too, when somebody
loves a place a great deal,

00:06:47.640 --> 00:06:48.810 align:middle line:90%
you know?

00:06:48.810 --> 00:06:50.307 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps the old
lady and gentleman

00:06:50.307 --> 00:06:52.890 align:middle line:84%
that bought their dream home and
they lived there for 50 years

00:06:52.890 --> 00:06:56.130 align:middle line:84%
and were blissfully happy there,
raised a family, they pass on.

00:06:56.130 --> 00:06:58.380 align:middle line:84%
Either they leave something
of themselves behind

00:06:58.380 --> 00:07:00.720 align:middle line:84%
or they come back and
visit, or so it seems.

00:07:00.720 --> 00:07:03.450 align:middle line:84%
Now the truth is, unfortunately,
those kind of stories

00:07:03.450 --> 00:07:05.880 align:middle line:84%
aren't great for headlines
and they're not popular.

00:07:05.880 --> 00:07:07.770 align:middle line:90%
Scary sells.

00:07:07.770 --> 00:07:11.080 align:middle line:84%
But they're every bit as
common, if not more so,

00:07:11.080 --> 00:07:14.220 align:middle line:84%
than some of the darker stuff,
and that's a wonderful thing.

00:07:14.220 --> 00:07:18.780 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I've got a house that
was built in 1926 in St. Louis,

00:07:18.780 --> 00:07:21.620 align:middle line:84%
and for a couple of years my
granddaughter lived there.

00:07:21.620 --> 00:07:25.200 align:middle line:84%
And I go back and forth between
St. Louis and Los Angeles.

00:07:25.200 --> 00:07:29.210 align:middle line:84%
And she would always say, Papa,
I see a little old man in here

00:07:29.210 --> 00:07:30.920 align:middle line:90%
sometimes at night.

00:07:30.920 --> 00:07:33.500 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, oh, come on, Ari.

00:07:33.500 --> 00:07:34.590 align:middle line:90%
What is this?

00:07:34.590 --> 00:07:36.440 align:middle line:84%
I haven't seen a
little old man there,

00:07:36.440 --> 00:07:39.980 align:middle line:84%
and I've been there
for 12, 13 years.

00:07:39.980 --> 00:07:43.310 align:middle line:84%
And then my daughter spent
the night there one night.

00:07:43.310 --> 00:07:47.460 align:middle line:84%
And she said, Dad,
did anybody ever

00:07:47.460 --> 00:07:50.760 align:middle line:84%
tell you about some kind of
little old man in this house?

00:07:50.760 --> 00:07:53.610 align:middle line:84%
And she had not talked to
my granddaughter about that.

00:07:53.610 --> 00:07:55.200 align:middle line:90%
It was her aunt.

00:07:55.200 --> 00:07:58.080 align:middle line:90%
And I said, uh, yeah.

00:07:58.080 --> 00:08:02.610 align:middle line:84%
And she described the same
kind of entity or being.

00:08:02.610 --> 00:08:04.405 align:middle line:84%
Something's here,
obviously, right?

00:08:04.405 --> 00:08:05.205 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Yeah.

00:08:05.205 --> 00:08:07.740 align:middle line:84%
And perhaps a former resident
of the home, you know?

00:08:07.740 --> 00:08:10.110 align:middle line:84%
Someone that was
happy there, someone

00:08:10.110 --> 00:08:12.840 align:middle line:84%
that went through the same
routine over and over again.

00:08:12.840 --> 00:08:16.020 align:middle line:84%
As Jeff said, sometimes you get
these less active hauntings,

00:08:16.020 --> 00:08:18.780 align:middle line:84%
and it's almost as if it's an
after echo of the person that

00:08:18.780 --> 00:08:19.860 align:middle line:90%
lived there, you know?

00:08:19.860 --> 00:08:21.970 align:middle line:84%
We get this glimpse
into the past.

00:08:21.970 --> 00:08:23.220 align:middle line:90%
Doesn't mean it's intelligent.

00:08:23.220 --> 00:08:24.930 align:middle line:84%
Doesn't mean there
is literally somebody

00:08:24.930 --> 00:08:27.480 align:middle line:84%
there that she could
communicate with any more

00:08:27.480 --> 00:08:30.120 align:middle line:84%
than you could communicate
with a picture on your TV set.

00:08:30.120 --> 00:08:32.250 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes it's just replaying
itself over and over

00:08:32.250 --> 00:08:35.010 align:middle line:84%
until that energy finally
Peters out and goes away.

00:08:35.010 --> 00:08:36.915 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why do
they wander around?

00:08:36.915 --> 00:08:38.530 align:middle line:90%
Why do they stay in the house?

00:08:38.530 --> 00:08:42.100 align:middle line:84%
Is it because they like
the place and they need it?

00:08:42.100 --> 00:08:43.390 align:middle line:90%
Don't they know they're dead?

00:08:43.390 --> 00:08:45.390 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: In the case of
an intelligent haunting,

00:08:45.390 --> 00:08:48.480 align:middle line:84%
I think that they're drawn
there or they stay there

00:08:48.480 --> 00:08:51.480 align:middle line:90%
for some kind of purpose.

00:08:51.480 --> 00:08:53.730 align:middle line:84%
The earliest haunting that
I'm aware of on record

00:08:53.730 --> 00:08:56.490 align:middle line:84%
takes us back to
ancient Rome, and it

00:08:56.490 --> 00:09:01.590 align:middle line:84%
was a house that was haunted
by the classic clanking chains

00:09:01.590 --> 00:09:03.370 align:middle line:84%
kind of ghost that
was trying to--

00:09:03.370 --> 00:09:04.170 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Scrooge.

00:09:04.170 --> 00:09:04.450 align:middle line:90%
Scrooge.

00:09:04.450 --> 00:09:06.270 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Very, very
similar to that, yeah.

00:09:06.270 --> 00:09:08.610 align:middle line:84%
But was trying to
indicate that its body had

00:09:08.610 --> 00:09:10.380 align:middle line:90%
been buried in the yard.

00:09:10.380 --> 00:09:11.790 align:middle line:84%
And once the body
was uncovered--

00:09:11.790 --> 00:09:13.770 align:middle line:84%
the ghost would walk
out into the yard

00:09:13.770 --> 00:09:15.960 align:middle line:84%
and residents of the
home were terrified.

00:09:15.960 --> 00:09:18.300 align:middle line:84%
They would never
follow this apparition.

00:09:18.300 --> 00:09:21.150 align:middle line:84%
Indicated that if they
dug in a certain spot,

00:09:21.150 --> 00:09:23.400 align:middle line:84%
they would find the body
of the murdered man.

00:09:23.400 --> 00:09:27.130 align:middle line:84%
And so the purpose in that
case was some kind of closure.

00:09:27.130 --> 00:09:27.930 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Aha.

00:09:27.930 --> 00:09:29.430 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And we
often see that there

00:09:29.430 --> 00:09:31.740 align:middle line:84%
is that kind of aha
moment in some hauntings.

00:09:31.740 --> 00:09:34.440 align:middle line:84%
Many seem to just want
acknowledgment, George.

00:09:34.440 --> 00:09:38.610 align:middle line:84%
But others are no more
aware of us than--

00:09:38.610 --> 00:09:41.040 align:middle line:84%
I should say, they can't
interact with us, you know?

00:09:41.040 --> 00:09:43.470 align:middle line:84%
I flip on my TV, I
see you on my screen,

00:09:43.470 --> 00:09:45.150 align:middle line:84%
you're not actually
in my living room.

00:09:45.150 --> 00:09:46.380 align:middle line:90%
It's an image of you.

00:09:46.380 --> 00:09:48.230 align:middle line:84%
And I think many
ghosts are that way.

00:09:48.230 --> 00:09:49.438 align:middle line:90%
They're a natural phenomenon.

00:09:49.438 --> 00:09:50.938 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: If someone
believes they're

00:09:50.938 --> 00:09:52.830 align:middle line:10%
living in a haunted
house and they need

00:09:52.830 --> 00:09:54.615 align:middle line:10%
some help, what do they do?

00:09:54.615 --> 00:09:57.240 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Well, the first thing
I really like to tell people is,

00:09:57.240 --> 00:09:58.650 align:middle line:90%
don't be afraid.

00:09:58.650 --> 00:10:00.720 align:middle line:90%
Do not live in fear, OK?

00:10:00.720 --> 00:10:03.220 align:middle line:84%
Because we are afraid
of the unknown.

00:10:03.220 --> 00:10:05.190 align:middle line:84%
But what I recommend
that you do is start

00:10:05.190 --> 00:10:08.220 align:middle line:84%
to keep a log of what strange
things happen at what times

00:10:08.220 --> 00:10:11.130 align:middle line:84%
of the day, because a reputable
paranormal investigator will

00:10:11.130 --> 00:10:13.190 align:middle line:84%
come in and will
look for patterns.

00:10:13.190 --> 00:10:15.420 align:middle line:84%
Do things always occur at
a certain time of the day

00:10:15.420 --> 00:10:16.920 align:middle line:90%
or at night?

00:10:16.920 --> 00:10:19.360 align:middle line:84%
I investigated one
case, for example,

00:10:19.360 --> 00:10:22.110 align:middle line:84%
where we found that the
reason the house was starting

00:10:22.110 --> 00:10:24.428 align:middle line:84%
to act strangely was that
they were on the main flight

00:10:24.428 --> 00:10:25.970 align:middle line:84%
path to Denver
International Airport.

00:10:25.970 --> 00:10:27.030 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Aha.

00:10:27.030 --> 00:10:29.760 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And we were able to
correlate these strange sounds

00:10:29.760 --> 00:10:32.010 align:middle line:84%
inside the house
with flight patterns

00:10:32.010 --> 00:10:35.100 align:middle line:84%
overhead, heavy aircraft
coming in to land.

00:10:35.100 --> 00:10:37.710 align:middle line:84%
So you know, I
recommend contacting

00:10:37.710 --> 00:10:39.420 align:middle line:84%
a reputable investigator,
but giving them

00:10:39.420 --> 00:10:41.550 align:middle line:90%
some data to work with.

00:10:41.550 --> 00:10:43.250 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's amazing.

00:10:43.250 --> 00:10:45.080 align:middle line:90%
And strange, too, isn't it?

00:10:45.080 --> 00:10:48.420 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: I think the
world works in very, very

00:10:48.420 --> 00:10:49.920 align:middle line:90%
many strange ways.

00:10:49.920 --> 00:10:51.750 align:middle line:84%
But I also think part
of the challenge,

00:10:51.750 --> 00:10:54.420 align:middle line:84%
part of the allure for
people that do what I do

00:10:54.420 --> 00:10:57.140 align:middle line:84%
is we like to try and
find those patterns,

00:10:57.140 --> 00:10:59.400 align:middle line:84%
and we like to solve
those mysteries.

00:10:59.400 --> 00:11:01.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: One of your shows
on the Travel Channel

00:11:01.590 --> 00:11:03.540 align:middle line:90%
is called "Haunted Hospitals."

00:11:03.540 --> 00:11:06.134 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about
these hospitals.

00:11:06.134 --> 00:11:07.098 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:07.098 --> 00:11:08.544 align:middle line:90%
[SIRENS]

00:11:08.544 --> 00:11:10.954 align:middle line:10%
[BEEPING]

00:11:10.954 --> 00:11:13.380 align:middle line:10%


00:11:13.380 --> 00:11:17.400 align:middle line:10%
>> What I loved most about
my job was helping people.

00:11:17.400 --> 00:11:20.820 align:middle line:10%
I wanted to be someone
who made a difference.

00:11:20.820 --> 00:11:23.490 align:middle line:10%
>> My goal of working at the
hospital was to stay there

00:11:23.490 --> 00:11:26.150 align:middle line:10%
and work there for a long time.

00:11:26.150 --> 00:11:27.962 align:middle line:10%
It did not work out that way.

00:11:27.962 --> 00:11:29.438 align:middle line:10%
[STATIC]

00:11:29.438 --> 00:11:31.898 align:middle line:10%
[MUTTERING]

00:11:31.898 --> 00:11:35.342 align:middle line:10%
[ANGRY WHISPERING]

00:11:35.342 --> 00:11:42.240 align:middle line:90%


00:11:42.240 --> 00:11:46.990 align:middle line:10%
>> I would feel this presence,
a sense of heaviness.

00:11:46.990 --> 00:11:48.710 align:middle line:10%
I felt an energy around me.

00:11:48.710 --> 00:11:53.156 align:middle line:90%


00:11:53.156 --> 00:11:54.144 align:middle line:10%
[GASP]

00:11:54.144 --> 00:11:57.640 align:middle line:90%


00:11:57.640 --> 00:12:01.750 align:middle line:10%
>> A hospital is one very
concentrated building.

00:12:01.750 --> 00:12:06.392 align:middle line:10%
People are dying and passing
from this life into the next.

00:12:06.392 --> 00:12:08.304 align:middle line:10%
>> Somebody's watching me.

00:12:08.304 --> 00:12:11.180 align:middle line:10%
>> Can you hear that?

00:12:11.180 --> 00:12:14.696 align:middle line:10%
>> And that leaves
behind a residue.

00:12:14.696 --> 00:12:15.680 align:middle line:10%
[BEEPING]

00:12:15.680 --> 00:12:17.156 align:middle line:10%
>> I'm one of the nurses here.

00:12:17.156 --> 00:12:18.140 align:middle line:10%
[WHOOSH]

00:12:18.140 --> 00:12:19.616 align:middle line:10%


00:12:19.616 --> 00:12:21.584 align:middle line:10%
(ANGRILY) I'll kill you.

00:12:21.584 --> 00:12:22.570 align:middle line:10%
[ROARING]

00:12:22.570 --> 00:12:27.140 align:middle line:10%
>> I did think to myself
that this woman is possessed.

00:12:27.140 --> 00:12:29.598 align:middle line:10%
>> That's when the cart
goes flying across the room.

00:12:29.598 --> 00:12:30.398 align:middle line:10%
[SCREAM]

00:12:30.398 --> 00:12:31.892 align:middle line:90%


00:12:31.892 --> 00:12:36.655 align:middle line:10%
>> The voice I heard
was not of the living.

00:12:36.655 --> 00:12:39.120 align:middle line:10%
[SCREAMING]

00:12:39.120 --> 00:12:44.460 align:middle line:10%
>> I have never seen anything
so foreboding in all of my life.

00:12:44.460 --> 00:12:45.933 align:middle line:10%
[CRASHING]

00:12:45.933 --> 00:12:48.570 align:middle line:10%


00:12:48.570 --> 00:12:49.370 align:middle line:10%
[ROAR]

00:12:49.370 --> 00:12:53.298 align:middle line:10%
[SCREAMING]

00:12:53.298 --> 00:12:54.280 align:middle line:10%


00:12:54.280 --> 00:12:56.450 align:middle line:10%
>> I understand why
people wouldn't believe,

00:12:56.450 --> 00:13:00.170 align:middle line:10%
and that's how I felt too, till
it actually happened to me.

00:13:00.170 --> 00:13:02.775 align:middle line:10%
And now nothing
will change my mind.

00:13:02.775 --> 00:13:03.650 align:middle line:90%
It's definitely real.

00:13:03.650 --> 00:13:04.450 align:middle line:90%


00:13:04.450 --> 00:13:07.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Richard,
what a creepy place.

00:13:07.040 --> 00:13:09.680 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And the truth is that
"Haunted Hospital" showcases

00:13:09.680 --> 00:13:11.180 align:middle line:84%
some of the more
frightening stories

00:13:11.180 --> 00:13:14.300 align:middle line:84%
that providers have that had
an emotional impact on them.

00:13:14.300 --> 00:13:17.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is that an ongoing
hospital, still open?

00:13:17.180 --> 00:13:18.860 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Actually,
there are-- we cover

00:13:18.860 --> 00:13:21.273 align:middle line:90%
39 different cases each season.

00:13:21.273 --> 00:13:22.190 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's a lot.

00:13:22.190 --> 00:13:24.080 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And some of them are
old and they're now-- yeah,

00:13:24.080 --> 00:13:24.480 align:middle line:90%
it is.

00:13:24.480 --> 00:13:25.010 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:13:25.010 --> 00:13:26.635 align:middle line:84%
Some of them are old
and now shut down.

00:13:26.635 --> 00:13:28.850 align:middle line:84%
Others, though, are
working, everyday hospitals.

00:13:28.850 --> 00:13:30.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I would hate
to be in that hospital.

00:13:30.980 --> 00:13:32.750 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: You know, again,
it comes back to the whole,

00:13:32.750 --> 00:13:33.560 align:middle line:90%
is it the hospital?

00:13:33.560 --> 00:13:36.200 align:middle line:90%
Is it the people involved?

00:13:36.200 --> 00:13:39.260 align:middle line:90%
When I became an EMT in 2002--

00:13:39.260 --> 00:13:42.240 align:middle line:84%
right after 9/11, I joined the
fire service and became an EMT.

00:13:42.240 --> 00:13:43.040 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You did.

00:13:43.040 --> 00:13:44.248 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for that.

00:13:44.248 --> 00:13:45.290 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: I appreciate it.

00:13:45.290 --> 00:13:46.250 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:13:46.250 --> 00:13:49.340 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't long before
I became that ghost guy

00:13:49.340 --> 00:13:52.143 align:middle line:84%
that I would have other EMTs
and paramedics and then nurses

00:13:52.143 --> 00:13:54.310 align:middle line:84%
and doctors, you know, oh,
you've got a ghost story.

00:13:54.310 --> 00:13:56.870 align:middle line:84%
Tell that ghost guy when
he brings a patient in.

00:13:56.870 --> 00:13:59.180 align:middle line:84%
And I realized that I was
hearing these stories from so

00:13:59.180 --> 00:14:00.807 align:middle line:90%
many medical professionals.

00:14:00.807 --> 00:14:02.640 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure over the
course of your career,

00:14:02.640 --> 00:14:06.003 align:middle line:84%
you've met many people
in the medical field.

00:14:06.003 --> 00:14:07.670 align:middle line:84%
And we're very close
to death, and we're

00:14:07.670 --> 00:14:10.670 align:middle line:84%
very close to those
extremes of emotion.

00:14:10.670 --> 00:14:12.740 align:middle line:84%
And I realized, this
is a huge phenomenon

00:14:12.740 --> 00:14:14.843 align:middle line:90%
within the medical community.

00:14:14.843 --> 00:14:16.760 align:middle line:84%
And many of them did not
want to be identified

00:14:16.760 --> 00:14:19.700 align:middle line:84%
when they shared their stories,
which makes me more impressed.

00:14:19.700 --> 00:14:22.490 align:middle line:84%
These weren't people that
were seeking to become famous.

00:14:22.490 --> 00:14:25.610 align:middle line:84%
They just wanted to say, this
strange thing happened to me.

00:14:25.610 --> 00:14:28.400 align:middle line:84%
I'll tell you, but
then I don't want

00:14:28.400 --> 00:14:30.478 align:middle line:84%
to be associated
with this publicly.

00:14:30.478 --> 00:14:32.270 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I had a call
from a police officer

00:14:32.270 --> 00:14:35.480 align:middle line:84%
on the radio show one day, and
they were the first responders.

00:14:35.480 --> 00:14:38.690 align:middle line:84%
They got there before
even the EMTs got there.

00:14:38.690 --> 00:14:41.990 align:middle line:84%
And the call was that somebody
was dying of a heart attack.

00:14:41.990 --> 00:14:43.460 align:middle line:90%
Get to this house.

00:14:43.460 --> 00:14:45.225 align:middle line:84%
So they got there
before the EMTs.

00:14:45.225 --> 00:14:46.100 align:middle line:90%
They get to the door.

00:14:46.100 --> 00:14:47.058 align:middle line:90%
They knock on the door.

00:14:47.058 --> 00:14:51.110 align:middle line:84%
A little man opens the door for
them and kind of shows them in.

00:14:51.110 --> 00:14:54.560 align:middle line:84%
And immediately on the
floor on his stomach

00:14:54.560 --> 00:14:59.630 align:middle line:84%
is somebody who obviously
is in distress or dying.

00:14:59.630 --> 00:15:00.650 align:middle line:90%
They get to him.

00:15:00.650 --> 00:15:01.820 align:middle line:90%
He's dead.

00:15:01.820 --> 00:15:03.740 align:middle line:90%
They turn him over.

00:15:03.740 --> 00:15:07.520 align:middle line:84%
It's the little old man who
opened the door to let them in.

00:15:07.520 --> 00:15:09.390 align:middle line:90%
How do you explain that?

00:15:09.390 --> 00:15:12.860 align:middle line:84%
And this was a police officer
who's calling the program,

00:15:12.860 --> 00:15:15.152 align:middle line:90%
and he's dead serious.

00:15:15.152 --> 00:15:17.110 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Has nothing to
gain by making this up,

00:15:17.110 --> 00:15:18.110 align:middle line:90%
by spinning a tale.

00:15:18.110 --> 00:15:18.980 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Nope.

00:15:18.980 --> 00:15:21.710 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And you know, doctors
are very rational people.

00:15:21.710 --> 00:15:25.220 align:middle line:84%
I always say that nurses are
the NCOs of the medical world.

00:15:25.220 --> 00:15:27.170 align:middle line:84%
They make hospitals
run in the same way

00:15:27.170 --> 00:15:28.790 align:middle line:84%
that sergeants
make the army run.

00:15:28.790 --> 00:15:30.590 align:middle line:84%
They'll tell you
what they think.

00:15:30.590 --> 00:15:32.780 align:middle line:84%
Doctors are a little
more circumspect,

00:15:32.780 --> 00:15:35.210 align:middle line:84%
but many doctors have
come to me over the years,

00:15:35.210 --> 00:15:38.000 align:middle line:84%
and they've said, you know, I
have a scientific background.

00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:40.400 align:middle line:84%
I don't believe in
this kind of hooey.

00:15:40.400 --> 00:15:41.590 align:middle line:90%
But this one time--

00:15:41.590 --> 00:15:42.390 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Uh-huh.

00:15:42.390 --> 00:15:44.870 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And they go on and
tell me this incredible--

00:15:44.870 --> 00:15:47.340 align:middle line:84%
And I would say, but how
do you explain that, doc?

00:15:47.340 --> 00:15:48.140 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Exactly.

00:15:48.140 --> 00:15:50.847 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And they say,
well, one of those things.

00:15:50.847 --> 00:15:52.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And they
still don't believe.

00:15:52.430 --> 00:15:53.230 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Right.

00:15:53.230 --> 00:15:54.540 align:middle line:90%
Or they don't think about it.

00:15:54.540 --> 00:15:56.930 align:middle line:84%
They don't want to
examine this too closely,

00:15:56.930 --> 00:15:59.330 align:middle line:84%
because as you're well aware
and your viewers are well

00:15:59.330 --> 00:16:03.320 align:middle line:84%
aware, if you start looking
into phenomena like this,

00:16:03.320 --> 00:16:06.440 align:middle line:84%
you realize the world is much
broader and stranger than most

00:16:06.440 --> 00:16:08.190 align:middle line:84%
people are comfortable
with acknowledging.

00:16:08.190 --> 00:16:09.200 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Absolutely.

