In the "Hospital" series, the
"Haunted Hospitals," what story

00:16:13.340 --> 00:16:16.852 align:middle line:84%
rings out for you that you
just will never forget?

00:16:16.852 --> 00:16:18.560 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Oh, that is
a terrific question.

00:16:18.560 --> 00:16:23.240 align:middle line:84%
It's one that my friend Kimm
Anderson brought to the show.

00:16:23.240 --> 00:16:27.630 align:middle line:84%
Kimm runs a haunted
house in Tooele, Utah.

00:16:27.630 --> 00:16:30.530 align:middle line:84%
And he does this for
the local children.

00:16:30.530 --> 00:16:34.400 align:middle line:84%
So this town has a community
of kids that really don't

00:16:34.400 --> 00:16:35.488 align:middle line:90%
have a lot of options as--

00:16:35.488 --> 00:16:38.030 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So they want to go to
haunted houses for fun, right?

00:16:38.030 --> 00:16:38.930 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Well, when
I say haunted house,

00:16:38.930 --> 00:16:41.180 align:middle line:84%
I mean the kind of
Halloween attraction

00:16:41.180 --> 00:16:42.887 align:middle line:90%
where you go to scare people.

00:16:42.887 --> 00:16:44.720 align:middle line:84%
And so these kids work
in the haunted house.

00:16:44.720 --> 00:16:46.490 align:middle line:84%
And so he bought
the local hospital

00:16:46.490 --> 00:16:49.570 align:middle line:84%
when it shut down and
turned it into a haunt.

00:16:49.570 --> 00:16:50.450 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Aha.

00:16:50.450 --> 00:16:53.327 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And the people
that left, they just

00:16:53.327 --> 00:16:54.410 align:middle line:90%
closed the doors and left.

00:16:54.410 --> 00:16:56.300 align:middle line:84%
They left the beds, they
left the X-ray machines.

00:16:56.300 --> 00:16:57.200 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They just
got out of there.

00:16:57.200 --> 00:16:58.610 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: They just
literally locked the doors

00:16:58.610 --> 00:17:00.460 align:middle line:84%
and walked out because
a newer hospital

00:17:00.460 --> 00:17:01.810 align:middle line:90%
had opened in the neighborhood.

00:17:01.810 --> 00:17:04.760 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't long before he
started running this place,

00:17:04.760 --> 00:17:07.130 align:middle line:84%
and people started
saying things like,

00:17:07.130 --> 00:17:10.369 align:middle line:84%
we loved your haunted house,
but the doctor in the emergency

00:17:10.369 --> 00:17:12.490 align:middle line:90%
department seemed really angry.

00:17:12.490 --> 00:17:14.420 align:middle line:84%
Like, really inappropriately
angry with us.

00:17:14.420 --> 00:17:16.790 align:middle line:84%
And he would have to say,
I didn't put a doctor

00:17:16.790 --> 00:17:18.345 align:middle line:90%
in the emergency department.

00:17:18.345 --> 00:17:20.720 align:middle line:84%
And then they would start
talking about a little girl who

00:17:20.720 --> 00:17:22.250 align:middle line:90%
was seen in the hallways.

00:17:22.250 --> 00:17:25.460 align:middle line:84%
And they would say,
she's a little young

00:17:25.460 --> 00:17:28.268 align:middle line:84%
to be working in a place
like this, don't you think?

00:17:28.268 --> 00:17:29.810 align:middle line:84%
And of course, this
was a little girl

00:17:29.810 --> 00:17:32.780 align:middle line:84%
that had died in the
hospital many years before.

00:17:32.780 --> 00:17:35.120 align:middle line:84%
And nine months of the
year, George, this hospital

00:17:35.120 --> 00:17:36.000 align:middle line:90%
is just shut down.

00:17:36.000 --> 00:17:36.800 align:middle line:90%
It's abandoned.

00:17:36.800 --> 00:17:37.880 align:middle line:90%
It's quiet.

00:17:37.880 --> 00:17:39.890 align:middle line:84%
Then around September,
people start coming in

00:17:39.890 --> 00:17:41.690 align:middle line:84%
for the Halloween
season, and they're all

00:17:41.690 --> 00:17:44.360 align:middle line:84%
coming in with the
intent of getting scared.

00:17:44.360 --> 00:17:47.870 align:middle line:84%
And the amount of energy
that this brings in I think

00:17:47.870 --> 00:17:49.947 align:middle line:84%
allows the spirits of
the hospital to manifest.

00:17:49.947 --> 00:17:50.780 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Absolutely.

00:17:50.780 --> 00:17:53.150 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: So I always
spend Halloween week

00:17:53.150 --> 00:17:54.670 align:middle line:90%
locked in that hospital.

00:17:54.670 --> 00:17:56.402 align:middle line:90%
I'm doing the same this year.

00:17:56.402 --> 00:17:58.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, you've heard
about the exorcist story,

00:17:58.610 --> 00:18:00.700 align:middle line:84%
the little boy from
Baltimore, Maryland,

00:18:00.700 --> 00:18:02.990 align:middle line:90%
that they turned into a movie.

00:18:02.990 --> 00:18:05.990 align:middle line:84%
The exorcism occurred
in St. Louis, Missouri,

00:18:05.990 --> 00:18:08.090 align:middle line:84%
at a hospital called
the Alexian Brothers

00:18:08.090 --> 00:18:10.130 align:middle line:90%
Hospital, which is no more.

00:18:10.130 --> 00:18:14.120 align:middle line:84%
But in that room where
they had the exorcism,

00:18:14.120 --> 00:18:17.720 align:middle line:84%
they decided, the hospital,
as it was closing down,

00:18:17.720 --> 00:18:21.680 align:middle line:84%
to sell off the furniture
that was in that room.

00:18:21.680 --> 00:18:25.440 align:middle line:84%
The bed, the little bureau,
and stuff like that.

00:18:25.440 --> 00:18:27.500 align:middle line:90%
So they got rid of it all.

00:18:27.500 --> 00:18:31.250 align:middle line:84%
People who bought the
furniture reported

00:18:31.250 --> 00:18:36.710 align:middle line:84%
horrible, horrible ghostly
stories attached to that.

00:18:36.710 --> 00:18:38.600 align:middle line:90%
I find that to be weird too.

00:18:38.600 --> 00:18:40.100 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And that
goes back to what

00:18:40.100 --> 00:18:42.800 align:middle line:84%
I said about haunted places,
haunted people, haunted

00:18:42.800 --> 00:18:43.760 align:middle line:90%
objects.

00:18:43.760 --> 00:18:45.380 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They attach
to everything.

00:18:45.380 --> 00:18:45.860 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Yeah.

00:18:45.860 --> 00:18:48.240 align:middle line:84%
And we talk about haunted
houses, but a lot of the time

00:18:48.240 --> 00:18:49.608 align:middle line:90%
it's not the house.

00:18:49.608 --> 00:18:51.650 align:middle line:84%
It's an artifact that was
brought into the house.

00:18:51.650 --> 00:18:56.220 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Your other show
is called "Paranormal 911."

00:18:56.220 --> 00:18:57.365 align:middle line:10%
>> Hello, 911.

00:18:57.365 --> 00:18:58.880 align:middle line:10%
>> Can you please help me?

00:18:58.880 --> 00:19:00.390 align:middle line:10%
Someone's trying
to get in my house.

00:19:00.390 --> 00:19:01.557 align:middle line:10%
>> OK, did you see a person?

00:19:01.557 --> 00:19:04.356 align:middle line:10%
Did you see, like, a
shadow of a person?

00:19:04.356 --> 00:19:05.904 align:middle line:10%
>> I have a gun in my hand.

00:19:05.904 --> 00:19:06.872 align:middle line:10%
I'm terrified.

00:19:06.872 --> 00:19:07.840 align:middle line:10%
[SCREAMS]

00:19:07.840 --> 00:19:10.750 align:middle line:10%
[SIRENS]

00:19:10.750 --> 00:19:13.450 align:middle line:10%
>> I've always wanted to help
people and make a difference

00:19:13.450 --> 00:19:14.830 align:middle line:10%
in somebody's life.

00:19:14.830 --> 00:19:17.620 align:middle line:10%
Paramedic and a firefighter,
that was my calling.

00:19:17.620 --> 00:19:20.590 align:middle line:10%
>> So within law enforcement,
you're expected to put yourself

00:19:20.590 --> 00:19:22.025 align:middle line:10%
in harm's way.

00:19:22.025 --> 00:19:24.400 align:middle line:10%
>> You go home knowing that
you did something that really

00:19:24.400 --> 00:19:27.372 align:middle line:10%
benefited the person
and/or the family.

00:19:27.372 --> 00:19:28.680 align:middle line:10%
>> (SHOUTING) Drop the gun!

00:19:28.680 --> 00:19:31.270 align:middle line:10%
>> The shootings, the stabbings,
the vital signs absent

00:19:31.270 --> 00:19:32.070 align:middle line:10%
patients.

00:19:32.070 --> 00:19:33.028 align:middle line:10%
Every call's different.

00:19:33.028 --> 00:19:33.828 align:middle line:10%
>> Come on, man.

00:19:33.828 --> 00:19:34.750 align:middle line:10%
Put it down.

00:19:34.750 --> 00:19:37.350 align:middle line:10%
>> Shoot me.

00:19:37.350 --> 00:19:39.690 align:middle line:10%
>> 911, state your emergency.

00:19:39.690 --> 00:19:41.254 align:middle line:10%
>> Can you come really fast?

00:19:41.254 --> 00:19:42.210 align:middle line:10%
Please, please!

00:19:42.210 --> 00:19:45.330 align:middle line:10%
>> Being a police officer,
I've dealt with a lot of life

00:19:45.330 --> 00:19:49.080 align:middle line:10%
and death situations, but I
can honestly say this one call

00:19:49.080 --> 00:19:51.742 align:middle line:10%
scared the living
shit out of me.

00:19:51.742 --> 00:19:52.554 align:middle line:10%
[SCREAMS]

00:19:52.554 --> 00:19:53.990 align:middle line:10%
>> That's my son right there.

00:19:53.990 --> 00:19:57.700 align:middle line:10%
He was killed in a
motorcycle accident.

00:19:57.700 --> 00:20:00.142 align:middle line:10%
>> Just put the gun down.

00:20:00.142 --> 00:20:01.114 align:middle line:10%
[GUNSHOT]

00:20:01.114 --> 00:20:04.516 align:middle line:90%


00:20:04.516 --> 00:20:05.488 align:middle line:90%
[GASP]

00:20:05.488 --> 00:20:06.177 align:middle line:90%


00:20:06.177 --> 00:20:08.260 align:middle line:10%
>> I said, I can't go to
work and talk about this,

00:20:08.260 --> 00:20:10.920 align:middle line:10%
because if I do, they're going
to put me in a psychiatric

00:20:10.920 --> 00:20:12.156 align:middle line:10%
ward.

00:20:12.156 --> 00:20:13.020 align:middle line:10%
>> Please hurry.

00:20:13.020 --> 00:20:13.880 align:middle line:10%
Please.

00:20:13.880 --> 00:20:14.850 align:middle line:10%
>> Just breathe, OK?

00:20:14.850 --> 00:20:16.790 align:middle line:10%
I'm going to stay with you on
the phone until they get there.

00:20:16.790 --> 00:20:19.165 align:middle line:10%
>> What happened to me that
night was something I'd never

00:20:19.165 --> 00:20:19.980 align:middle line:10%
experienced before.

00:20:19.980 --> 00:20:21.083 align:middle line:10%
[WHOOSH]

00:20:21.083 --> 00:20:23.500 align:middle line:10%
>> I did realize with that
figure that it wasn't something

00:20:23.500 --> 00:20:24.300 align:middle line:10%
in this world.

00:20:24.300 --> 00:20:26.078 align:middle line:10%
[ROARING]

00:20:26.078 --> 00:20:28.066 align:middle line:10%


00:20:28.066 --> 00:20:29.060 align:middle line:10%
[SCREAM]

00:20:29.060 --> 00:20:30.054 align:middle line:10%
>> Make sure you're OK.

00:20:30.054 --> 00:20:32.539 align:middle line:10%
[GROWLING]

00:20:32.539 --> 00:20:33.533 align:middle line:10%
You see that?

00:20:33.533 --> 00:20:38.503 align:middle line:90%


00:20:38.503 --> 00:20:39.994 align:middle line:10%
>> But I'm a believer now.

00:20:39.994 --> 00:20:44.467 align:middle line:10%
[TENSE MUSIC]

00:20:44.467 --> 00:20:46.952 align:middle line:10%
>> Do you have an emergency?

00:20:46.952 --> 00:20:47.946 align:middle line:10%
[CREAKING]

00:20:47.946 --> 00:20:51.922 align:middle line:90%


00:20:51.922 --> 00:20:54.960 align:middle line:10%
>> (SHOUTING) Hello?

00:20:54.960 --> 00:20:55.800 align:middle line:10%
Dispatch!

00:20:55.800 --> 00:20:59.090 align:middle line:10%
[CRYING]

00:20:59.090 --> 00:21:01.440 align:middle line:90%


00:21:01.440 --> 00:21:02.500 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Jeez.

00:21:02.500 --> 00:21:03.480 align:middle line:90%
Great show.

00:21:03.480 --> 00:21:04.280 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Thank you.

00:21:04.280 --> 00:21:05.650 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's scary
as all get out.

00:21:05.650 --> 00:21:07.775 align:middle line:10%
>>ESTEP: And you know, what
interests me about this

00:21:07.775 --> 00:21:11.950 align:middle line:10%
is that paramedics, EMTs,
police officers, firefighters,

00:21:11.950 --> 00:21:14.440 align:middle line:10%
all trained to keep
their heads in a crisis.

00:21:14.440 --> 00:21:16.300 align:middle line:90%
All trained to be calm.

00:21:16.300 --> 00:21:19.300 align:middle line:84%
When everybody else is running
away, we're running in.

00:21:19.300 --> 00:21:22.210 align:middle line:84%
So when these people tell
me their strange stories,

00:21:22.210 --> 00:21:24.950 align:middle line:84%
there's a huge stigma in the
emergency services community

00:21:24.950 --> 00:21:26.610 align:middle line:90%
of seeing ghosts, you know?

00:21:26.610 --> 00:21:29.870 align:middle line:84%
As the lady said, I can't go
to work and talk about this,

00:21:29.870 --> 00:21:32.020 align:middle line:84%
or they'd put me in
a mental institution.

00:21:32.020 --> 00:21:33.005 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: She's right.

00:21:33.005 --> 00:21:33.910 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: She is.

00:21:33.910 --> 00:21:36.255 align:middle line:84%
And so only recently
have these people

00:21:36.255 --> 00:21:38.380 align:middle line:84%
been a little more comfortable
about coming forward

00:21:38.380 --> 00:21:39.970 align:middle line:90%
and telling their stories.

00:21:39.970 --> 00:21:41.702 align:middle line:84%
Often, they'll do it
after they retire.

00:21:41.702 --> 00:21:43.660 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tell me about
"Paranormal Nightshift."

00:21:43.660 --> 00:21:44.500 align:middle line:90%
What is that?

00:21:44.500 --> 00:21:45.820 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: "Paranormal
Nightshift" is

00:21:45.820 --> 00:21:48.160 align:middle line:84%
a show from the same producers
that I'm involved with.

00:21:48.160 --> 00:21:51.160 align:middle line:84%
And really, after
"Paranormal 911,"

00:21:51.160 --> 00:21:54.100 align:middle line:84%
we realized that a lot of people
who work the graveyard shift

00:21:54.100 --> 00:21:55.750 align:middle line:90%
have their own strange stories.

00:21:55.750 --> 00:21:58.998 align:middle line:84%
When most people are in bed,
the rest of society is sleeping,

00:21:58.998 --> 00:22:01.540 align:middle line:84%
we know that the world is still
running, that there are still

00:22:01.540 --> 00:22:03.520 align:middle line:84%
those clerks, there are
those delivery people,

00:22:03.520 --> 00:22:05.350 align:middle line:90%
security guards, cleaners.

00:22:05.350 --> 00:22:09.170 align:middle line:84%
And they are experiencing
strange things,

00:22:09.170 --> 00:22:11.622 align:middle line:84%
and some of them are coming
to tell us their stories.

00:22:11.622 --> 00:22:13.830 align:middle line:84%
And that's what "Paranormal
Nightshift" is all about.

00:22:13.830 --> 00:22:15.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That should
be another great show.

00:22:15.670 --> 00:22:17.740 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Coming later this year,
we hope to the Travel Channel.

00:22:17.740 --> 00:22:18.730 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Absolutely.

00:22:18.730 --> 00:22:21.280 align:middle line:84%
Well, let us know what we can
do for you on the radio show

00:22:21.280 --> 00:22:22.688 align:middle line:90%
to help promote that.

00:22:22.688 --> 00:22:24.980 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Always happy to come
talk to you on the radio.

00:22:24.980 --> 00:22:28.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What is it about
these apparitions that

00:22:28.180 --> 00:22:31.490 align:middle line:90%
are so scary to so many people?

00:22:31.490 --> 00:22:34.280 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: I think that,
again, we fear the unknown.

00:22:34.280 --> 00:22:37.850 align:middle line:84%
And when it comes to
these sorts of phenomena,

00:22:37.850 --> 00:22:40.430 align:middle line:84%
you can watch as many movies
as you like, read as many books

00:22:40.430 --> 00:22:42.140 align:middle line:90%
as you like.

00:22:42.140 --> 00:22:44.540 align:middle line:84%
You never truly believe
until it happens to you.

00:22:44.540 --> 00:22:47.150 align:middle line:84%
I mean, deep down
at a visceral level,

00:22:47.150 --> 00:22:50.330 align:middle line:84%
you don't truly believe this
stuff until it happens to you.

00:22:50.330 --> 00:22:53.150 align:middle line:84%
So those that do
see apparitions,

00:22:53.150 --> 00:22:55.410 align:middle line:84%
it rocks the foundation
of their world.

00:22:55.410 --> 00:22:59.260 align:middle line:84%
It changes the way they look
at everything, fundamentally.

00:22:59.260 --> 00:23:01.490 align:middle line:84%
And for some, it's a
source of great fear.

00:23:01.490 --> 00:23:04.353 align:middle line:84%
But once that fear goes away,
many of these folks I talk to,

00:23:04.353 --> 00:23:06.020 align:middle line:84%
they'll tell me their
life is actually--

00:23:06.020 --> 00:23:07.700 align:middle line:90%
their worldview is broadened.

00:23:07.700 --> 00:23:09.680 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if that's been your
experience with the folks you--

00:23:09.680 --> 00:23:10.850 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Same thing too.

00:23:10.850 --> 00:23:12.140 align:middle line:90%
But it makes you a believer.

00:23:12.140 --> 00:23:13.010 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: It does.

00:23:13.010 --> 00:23:15.750 align:middle line:84%
And again, you know, you
can believe in many things,

00:23:15.750 --> 00:23:17.750 align:middle line:84%
but until there's
that visceral gut

00:23:17.750 --> 00:23:22.340 align:middle line:84%
punch of it happening to
you, you won't truly believe.

00:23:22.340 --> 00:23:23.300 align:middle line:90%
I think, anyway.

00:23:23.300 --> 00:23:25.650 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You know,
poor law enforcement,

00:23:25.650 --> 00:23:27.440 align:middle line:90%
including yourself.

00:23:27.440 --> 00:23:29.120 align:middle line:84%
They're under so much
pressure with all

00:23:29.120 --> 00:23:31.940 align:middle line:84%
these other outside
situations that they

00:23:31.940 --> 00:23:34.550 align:middle line:84%
have to be confronted
by these things.

00:23:34.550 --> 00:23:35.925 align:middle line:90%
That's unbelievable.

00:23:35.925 --> 00:23:37.550 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And I'm
always willing to talk

00:23:37.550 --> 00:23:39.350 align:middle line:90%
to anybody that wears a badge.

00:23:39.350 --> 00:23:41.218 align:middle line:90%
Or not, but still.

00:23:41.218 --> 00:23:43.760 align:middle line:84%
They can call me or contact me
or email me with their stories

00:23:43.760 --> 00:23:44.622 align:middle line:90%
at any time.

00:23:44.622 --> 00:23:46.580 align:middle line:84%
And one of the most
important things you can do

00:23:46.580 --> 00:23:49.580 align:middle line:90%
is just listen and accept.

00:23:49.580 --> 00:23:50.650 align:middle line:90%
But I'm still working.

00:23:50.650 --> 00:23:54.490 align:middle line:84%
I'm still a paramedic,
here locally in fact.

00:23:54.490 --> 00:23:58.460 align:middle line:84%
And I still get stories from
officers and from EMS providers

00:23:58.460 --> 00:23:59.570 align:middle line:90%
and firefighters.

00:23:59.570 --> 00:24:02.150 align:middle line:84%
And they'll say, you know,
don't quote me on this.

00:24:02.150 --> 00:24:04.940 align:middle line:84%
I just-- I figured
you would believe me.

00:24:04.940 --> 00:24:07.880 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I had an EMT
caller a couple years ago

00:24:07.880 --> 00:24:11.510 align:middle line:90%
who was driving in her car.

00:24:11.510 --> 00:24:13.040 align:middle line:90%
She wasn't on duty.

00:24:13.040 --> 00:24:18.080 align:middle line:84%
Came across an accident and
saw a body outside of the car.

00:24:18.080 --> 00:24:20.180 align:middle line:84%
And it was a single
car accident.

00:24:20.180 --> 00:24:23.140 align:middle line:90%
And she jumped out, and she's--

00:24:23.140 --> 00:24:25.610 align:middle line:84%
you know, her cell
phone's in her car.

00:24:25.610 --> 00:24:26.840 align:middle line:90%
She's looking at the body.

00:24:26.840 --> 00:24:30.020 align:middle line:84%
She sees somebody standing
on the side of the road,

00:24:30.020 --> 00:24:33.530 align:middle line:84%
screaming at him,
going, call 911, please.

00:24:33.530 --> 00:24:35.390 align:middle line:90%
Call 911.

00:24:35.390 --> 00:24:39.160 align:middle line:84%
She realized again
that was the body.

00:24:39.160 --> 00:24:42.530 align:middle line:84%
He'd already died and was
ghostly, standing on the side,

00:24:42.530 --> 00:24:43.550 align:middle line:90%
just watching.

00:24:43.550 --> 00:24:45.675 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: I wrote a book
called "Haunted Healthcare"

00:24:45.675 --> 00:24:49.070 align:middle line:84%
and talked to a nurse that was
involved with a resuscitation

00:24:49.070 --> 00:24:51.500 align:middle line:84%
in which a-- it's
a very sad story--

00:24:51.500 --> 00:24:55.295 align:middle line:84%
the driver of a car had
hit a family of four and--

00:24:55.295 --> 00:24:56.160 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, god.

00:24:56.160 --> 00:24:56.960 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Yeah.

00:24:56.960 --> 00:24:57.918 align:middle line:90%
And he had been killed.

00:24:57.918 --> 00:25:02.610 align:middle line:84%
The driver had been killed,
as had members of the family.

00:25:02.610 --> 00:25:05.420 align:middle line:84%
And as the nurses,
physicians, and technicians

00:25:05.420 --> 00:25:07.460 align:middle line:84%
in the ED, the
Emergency Department,

00:25:07.460 --> 00:25:10.310 align:middle line:84%
were resuscitating one
of the family members,

00:25:10.310 --> 00:25:13.550 align:middle line:84%
some but not all of them noticed
a gentleman standing back

00:25:13.550 --> 00:25:16.100 align:middle line:84%
against the far wall
of the emergency room.

00:25:16.100 --> 00:25:17.060 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: There he was.

00:25:17.060 --> 00:25:18.018 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: And that's it.

00:25:18.018 --> 00:25:21.020 align:middle line:84%
So they all assumed, maybe this
is just a family member that

00:25:21.020 --> 00:25:22.520 align:middle line:90%
came in or was in the car.

00:25:22.520 --> 00:25:23.630 align:middle line:90%
We'll get to you later.

00:25:23.630 --> 00:25:24.692 align:middle line:90%
We're working here.

00:25:24.692 --> 00:25:26.150 align:middle line:84%
And it was only
later they realized

00:25:26.150 --> 00:25:29.420 align:middle line:84%
it was the driver of the car
that hit the family whose

00:25:29.420 --> 00:25:31.520 align:middle line:84%
body was in the room
next door and had just

00:25:31.520 --> 00:25:32.450 align:middle line:90%
been pronounced dead.

00:25:32.450 --> 00:25:33.650 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wow.

00:25:33.650 --> 00:25:34.910 align:middle line:90%
That's just real stuff.

00:25:34.910 --> 00:25:35.710 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Yeah.

00:25:35.710 --> 00:25:39.410 align:middle line:84%
And what fascinates me is,
why do only half of the people

00:25:39.410 --> 00:25:42.470 align:middle line:84%
in the room notice this
guy, and why do half not?

00:25:42.470 --> 00:25:44.990 align:middle line:84%
Because we still don't know
how people see ghosts, George.

00:25:44.990 --> 00:25:45.720 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's a good point.

00:25:45.720 --> 00:25:47.220 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: I'm actually
of the opinion

00:25:47.220 --> 00:25:48.590 align:middle line:90%
that we don't see them at all.

00:25:48.590 --> 00:25:51.275 align:middle line:84%
I think we perceive them
by some other means.

00:25:51.275 --> 00:25:53.400 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Some people are
more sensitive than others

00:25:53.400 --> 00:25:54.698 align:middle line:90%
and they pick up on this.

00:25:54.698 --> 00:25:56.240 align:middle line:84%
How many books do
you have out there?

00:25:56.240 --> 00:25:57.200 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: It's 20-something now.

00:25:57.200 --> 00:25:58.130 align:middle line:90%
I'm embarrassed to give you--

00:25:58.130 --> 00:25:59.160 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: 20-some books?

00:25:59.160 --> 00:25:59.960 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Yeah.

00:25:59.960 --> 00:26:01.130 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Whoa.

00:26:01.130 --> 00:26:03.050 align:middle line:90%
How are you so prolific?

00:26:03.050 --> 00:26:04.190 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: I love to write.

00:26:04.190 --> 00:26:05.830 align:middle line:90%
I write every day.

00:26:05.830 --> 00:26:08.330 align:middle line:84%
I don't sleep well unless I've
written about thousand words.

00:26:08.330 --> 00:26:11.855 align:middle line:84%
But the secret is it doesn't
feel like work to me, you know?

00:26:11.855 --> 00:26:15.230 align:middle line:84%
I'm living these adventures
in haunted locations,

00:26:15.230 --> 00:26:18.052 align:middle line:84%
and then I get to come and
just recall them for people

00:26:18.052 --> 00:26:19.010 align:middle line:90%
that want to read them.

00:26:19.010 --> 00:26:21.410 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are they
all haunted-related?

00:26:21.410 --> 00:26:23.570 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Until this year, yeah.

00:26:23.570 --> 00:26:26.060 align:middle line:84%
They've all been
haunted-related.

00:26:26.060 --> 00:26:28.920 align:middle line:84%
I just finished my first
non-paranormal book,

00:26:28.920 --> 00:26:31.970 align:middle line:84%
which is a big 150,000-word
overview of some

00:26:31.970 --> 00:26:34.310 align:middle line:90%
of the world's serial killers.

00:26:34.310 --> 00:26:36.200 align:middle line:84%
And my newest
contracted project is

00:26:36.200 --> 00:26:37.790 align:middle line:90%
a history of the US military.

00:26:37.790 --> 00:26:38.120 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Uh-huh.

00:26:38.120 --> 00:26:38.780 align:middle line:90%
That's interesting.

00:26:38.780 --> 00:26:39.860 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: No ghosts there.

00:26:39.860 --> 00:26:41.660 align:middle line:90%
Well, maybe I'll sneak one in.

00:26:41.660 --> 00:26:44.300 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So the subject matter,
the hauntings that you go on

00:26:44.300 --> 00:26:46.710 align:middle line:90%
then turn into books primarily?

00:26:46.710 --> 00:26:47.510 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Yeah.

00:26:47.510 --> 00:26:50.650 align:middle line:84%
I like to move into a
haunted location if possible,

00:26:50.650 --> 00:26:54.060 align:middle line:84%
spend several days
there around the clock.

00:26:54.060 --> 00:26:56.090 align:middle line:84%
It's my belief--
and I learned this

00:26:56.090 --> 00:26:58.050 align:middle line:84%
back in fire academy
many years ago.

00:26:58.050 --> 00:27:00.300 align:middle line:84%
Firefighters will tell you,
the enemy is not the fire,

00:27:00.300 --> 00:27:00.980 align:middle line:90%
it's the building.

00:27:00.980 --> 00:27:02.180 align:middle line:84%
The building is
what'll kill you.

00:27:02.180 --> 00:27:03.040 align:middle line:90%
It's your battleground.

00:27:03.040 --> 00:27:03.957 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's right.

00:27:03.957 --> 00:27:06.665 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: So firefighters
study construction.

00:27:06.665 --> 00:27:09.040 align:middle line:84%
We're interested in the way
air moves through a building.

00:27:09.040 --> 00:27:10.545 align:middle line:84%
We're interested in
how buildings behave.

00:27:10.545 --> 00:27:11.837 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What the floor's like.

00:27:11.837 --> 00:27:12.900 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Exactly, yeah.

00:27:12.900 --> 00:27:15.870 align:middle line:84%
The camber of the floor,
the way things are laid out.

00:27:15.870 --> 00:27:18.330 align:middle line:84%
And it takes a good
24 hours in a place

00:27:18.330 --> 00:27:21.473 align:middle line:84%
to understand a
structure, you know?

00:27:21.473 --> 00:27:22.890 align:middle line:84%
We've got some hot
days right now.

00:27:22.890 --> 00:27:23.730 align:middle line:90%
It's June.

00:27:23.730 --> 00:27:27.060 align:middle line:84%
So buildings like this will heat
up today, and then tonight when

00:27:27.060 --> 00:27:28.530 align:middle line:90%
it cools, they'll contract.

00:27:28.530 --> 00:27:29.460 align:middle line:90%
They'll creak.

00:27:29.460 --> 00:27:31.710 align:middle line:84%
Phantom footsteps on
the floor above you,

00:27:31.710 --> 00:27:34.480 align:middle line:84%
except it's just the
house contracting.

00:27:34.480 --> 00:27:36.630 align:middle line:84%
So I like to do that
for my first 24 hours,

00:27:36.630 --> 00:27:37.920 align:middle line:90%
just get to know the building.

00:27:37.920 --> 00:27:38.460 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: OK.

00:27:38.460 --> 00:27:40.530 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Then we have a
baseline to start testing

00:27:40.530 --> 00:27:42.630 align:middle line:90%
some of these anomalous claims.

00:27:42.630 --> 00:27:45.880 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What if it's not the
house contracting, but actually

00:27:45.880 --> 00:27:46.680 align:middle line:90%
footsteps?

00:27:46.680 --> 00:27:48.690 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: That's why
we're really there.

00:27:48.690 --> 00:27:50.610 align:middle line:84%
I would tell you
frankly that 90%

00:27:50.610 --> 00:27:53.700 align:middle line:84%
of my time as a paranormal
investigator is wasted.

00:27:53.700 --> 00:27:57.250 align:middle line:84%
I spend 90% of my time
waiting for 10% to happen.

00:27:57.250 --> 00:27:58.050 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yes.

00:27:58.050 --> 00:27:58.980 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: You know?

00:27:58.980 --> 00:28:02.100 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But that 10%
makes it worth waiting for.

00:28:02.100 --> 00:28:04.470 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And that
honestly parallels my time

00:28:04.470 --> 00:28:06.750 align:middle line:84%
in the fire service and
in emergency medicine.

00:28:06.750 --> 00:28:10.350 align:middle line:84%
90% of what we do is
not a true emergency.

00:28:10.350 --> 00:28:14.280 align:middle line:84%
But the 10% that is
makes it rewarding work,

00:28:14.280 --> 00:28:15.150 align:middle line:90%
more rewarding work.

00:28:15.150 --> 00:28:17.220 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you get a call
sometimes and you just

00:28:17.220 --> 00:28:19.205 align:middle line:84%
get there and go,
why did they call us?

00:28:19.205 --> 00:28:20.580 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: You know,
I'll tell you.

00:28:20.580 --> 00:28:22.620 align:middle line:90%
Most paramedics do.

00:28:22.620 --> 00:28:24.420 align:middle line:84%
But the way to look at
this, and the reason

00:28:24.420 --> 00:28:26.835 align:middle line:84%
that I've done this
for 17 years now

00:28:26.835 --> 00:28:29.190 align:middle line:84%
and will hopefully go
on to do it much longer

00:28:29.190 --> 00:28:32.570 align:middle line:84%
is that there is no such
thing as an unimportant call.

00:28:32.570 --> 00:28:34.310 align:middle line:84%
It might not be an
emergency to me--

00:28:34.310 --> 00:28:34.640 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:28:34.640 --> 00:28:36.220 align:middle line:84%
But it may not be
important to you.

00:28:36.220 --> 00:28:37.720 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: But it
may-- yeah, exactly.

00:28:37.720 --> 00:28:39.590 align:middle line:84%
But it becomes
important, because I

00:28:39.590 --> 00:28:42.380 align:middle line:84%
would say the most important
thing I ever do in medicine

00:28:42.380 --> 00:28:44.432 align:middle line:90%
is hold a lonely person's hand.

00:28:44.432 --> 00:28:45.890 align:middle line:84%
They call us because
it's the worst

00:28:45.890 --> 00:28:47.240 align:middle line:90%
day they're ever going to have.

00:28:47.240 --> 00:28:49.730 align:middle line:84%
And we have the
privilege of trying

00:28:49.730 --> 00:28:53.330 align:middle line:84%
to make that better, or at
least suck a little bit less.

00:28:53.330 --> 00:28:56.517 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do they ever follow
up and thank you and find you?

00:28:56.517 --> 00:28:58.100 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: I'll be
shopping in the store

00:28:58.100 --> 00:29:01.083 align:middle line:84%
and someone will come
up to me and say hello.

00:29:01.083 --> 00:29:02.750 align:middle line:84%
And it will take me
a moment to realize,

00:29:02.750 --> 00:29:06.190 align:middle line:84%
the last time I saw them they
were significantly unwell.

00:29:06.190 --> 00:29:06.990 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:29:06.990 --> 00:29:08.300 align:middle line:90%
It does happen.

00:29:08.300 --> 00:29:10.010 align:middle line:90%
Medicine is a rewarding job.

00:29:10.010 --> 00:29:11.030 align:middle line:90%
It really is.

00:29:11.030 --> 00:29:13.080 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What do you
think of serial killers?

00:29:13.080 --> 00:29:15.530 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: I think they're are
a lot more prevalent than we

00:29:15.530 --> 00:29:16.990 align:middle line:90%
give credit for.

00:29:16.990 --> 00:29:19.070 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: The FBI says
there are many wandering

00:29:19.070 --> 00:29:20.405 align:middle line:90%
this planet right now.

00:29:20.405 --> 00:29:22.280 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Yeah, and the
smart ones, of course,

00:29:22.280 --> 00:29:23.867 align:middle line:90%
don't get caught.

00:29:23.867 --> 00:29:25.450 align:middle line:84%
So it's the ones
that get away with it

00:29:25.450 --> 00:29:28.585 align:middle line:84%
that are perhaps the most
interesting and alarming.

00:29:28.585 --> 00:29:29.960 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Recently,
I had a chance

00:29:29.960 --> 00:29:32.360 align:middle line:84%
to interview a
conspiracy researcher,

00:29:32.360 --> 00:29:35.510 align:middle line:84%
Olav Phillips, about
the Zodiac killer.

00:29:35.510 --> 00:29:38.765 align:middle line:84%
And he had some astounding
things to tell us.

00:29:38.765 --> 00:29:41.612 align:middle line:10%
What other strange occurrences
when you were investigating?

00:29:41.612 --> 00:29:43.070 align:middle line:10%
>>OLAV PHILLIPS:
We had flashlights

00:29:43.070 --> 00:29:45.020 align:middle line:10%
that would turn on and off.

00:29:45.020 --> 00:29:48.440 align:middle line:10%
We actually got to a
point where we had set up

00:29:48.440 --> 00:29:52.280 align:middle line:10%
a series of flashlights, and
we could ask him questions

00:29:52.280 --> 00:29:55.040 align:middle line:10%
and get him to turn the
flashlights on and off.

00:29:55.040 --> 00:29:56.532 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: And you
felt his presence?

00:29:56.532 --> 00:29:58.740 align:middle line:10%
>> PHILLIPS: The temperature--
once he became active,

00:29:58.740 --> 00:30:01.528 align:middle line:10%
the temperature in the place
dropped by at least 15 degrees.

00:30:01.528 --> 00:30:03.570 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Of all the suspects
that are out there--

00:30:03.570 --> 00:30:07.920 align:middle line:10%
and like I said, there's
a handful of them--

00:30:07.920 --> 00:30:11.900 align:middle line:10%
would you say that he might
have been the biggest suspect?

00:30:11.900 --> 00:30:15.650 align:middle line:10%
>> PHILLIPS: Listening to
him talk on the SB7, I mean,

00:30:15.650 --> 00:30:16.640 align:middle line:10%
it's very pointed.

00:30:16.640 --> 00:30:18.440 align:middle line:10%
He says, I am the Zodiac.

00:30:18.440 --> 00:30:20.290 align:middle line:10%
He was very clear.

00:30:20.290 --> 00:30:23.390 align:middle line:10%
And all the communications
that we had through the SB7

00:30:23.390 --> 00:30:26.570 align:middle line:10%
were in other ways
that were very clear.

00:30:26.570 --> 00:30:28.340 align:middle line:10%
His intent was very clear.

00:30:28.340 --> 00:30:30.710 align:middle line:10%
When I was in that building--

00:30:30.710 --> 00:30:32.000 align:middle line:10%
and it's not a big building.

00:30:32.000 --> 00:30:32.810 align:middle line:10%
But when I was in
that building--

00:30:32.810 --> 00:30:34.190 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: And that
building's still there?

00:30:34.190 --> 00:30:35.000 align:middle line:10%
>> PHILLIPS: The
building's still there.

00:30:35.000 --> 00:30:35.670 align:middle line:10%
Yep.

00:30:35.670 --> 00:30:37.370 align:middle line:10%
And the newspaper's
still in the building.

00:30:37.370 --> 00:30:39.287 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Did it scare
you when you were there?

00:30:39.287 --> 00:30:40.273 align:middle line:10%
>> PHILLIPS: Yes.

00:30:40.273 --> 00:30:41.690 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: And you
don't get scared.

00:30:41.690 --> 00:30:42.650 align:middle line:10%
>> PHILLIPS: No.

00:30:42.650 --> 00:30:46.350 align:middle line:10%
More than any haunted
location I've ever been to,

00:30:46.350 --> 00:30:47.610 align:middle line:10%
you could just feel it.

00:30:47.610 --> 00:30:48.410 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Evil.

00:30:48.410 --> 00:30:50.450 align:middle line:10%
>> PHILLIPS: You could
feel the malevolence.

00:30:50.450 --> 00:30:52.720 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: Pure evil.

00:30:52.720 --> 00:30:54.470 align:middle line:10%
>> PHILLIPS: And when
he was doing things,

00:30:54.470 --> 00:30:56.120 align:middle line:10%
he was messing with you.

00:30:56.120 --> 00:30:58.490 align:middle line:10%
And you knew that he
was messing with you.

00:30:58.490 --> 00:31:02.870 align:middle line:10%
You knew that he was
there and he wanted--

00:31:02.870 --> 00:31:05.037 align:middle line:10%
he was after you.

00:31:05.037 --> 00:31:07.620 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you feel pure evil,
Richard, sometimes when you're

00:31:07.620 --> 00:31:10.070 align:middle line:90%
in these situations?

00:31:10.070 --> 00:31:12.570 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: You know, I didn't
used to see it that way, George.

00:31:12.570 --> 00:31:14.880 align:middle line:84%
But I've worked a number
of cases in which I

00:31:14.880 --> 00:31:16.470 align:middle line:90%
start to question that.

00:31:16.470 --> 00:31:18.330 align:middle line:90%
Perhaps the most recent one--

00:31:18.330 --> 00:31:21.210 align:middle line:84%
and I can kind of report a
similar experience to Olav--

00:31:21.210 --> 00:31:24.000 align:middle line:84%
was in the Villisca Ax
Murder House in Iowa,

00:31:24.000 --> 00:31:26.580 align:middle line:84%
which is one of the books
I'm finishing this year.

00:31:26.580 --> 00:31:28.920 align:middle line:84%
And if you're not familiar
with those murders,

00:31:28.920 --> 00:31:31.350 align:middle line:84%
this is the story that
actually knocked the Titanic

00:31:31.350 --> 00:31:33.090 align:middle line:84%
off the front pages
of US newspapers.

00:31:33.090 --> 00:31:33.990 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, really?

00:31:33.990 --> 00:31:34.300 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Somebody--

00:31:34.300 --> 00:31:35.730 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's a huge story.

00:31:35.730 --> 00:31:37.110 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: It was massive.

00:31:37.110 --> 00:31:39.390 align:middle line:84%
Person or persons--
there is a debate--

00:31:39.390 --> 00:31:43.440 align:middle line:84%
unknown walked into a house in
this tiny town, Villisca, Iowa,

00:31:43.440 --> 00:31:46.590 align:middle line:84%
and took the family's
own ax from the woodpile.

00:31:46.590 --> 00:31:48.780 align:middle line:84%
It's believed the killer
was hiding in the barn.

00:31:48.780 --> 00:31:50.940 align:middle line:84%
Broke in after the
family had gone to bed,

00:31:50.940 --> 00:31:54.270 align:middle line:84%
murdered the parents in their
bed, and then six children

00:31:54.270 --> 00:31:57.445 align:middle line:90%
also, all with this ax.

00:31:57.445 --> 00:31:59.070 align:middle line:84%
The Villisca Ax Murder
House is kind of

00:31:59.070 --> 00:32:01.768 align:middle line:84%
unique in that most
scenes of murders

00:32:01.768 --> 00:32:02.810 align:middle line:90%
like that are demolished.

00:32:02.810 --> 00:32:04.720 align:middle line:90%
They're pulled down.

00:32:04.720 --> 00:32:07.380 align:middle line:84%
But that house stands pretty
much today as it was then.

00:32:07.380 --> 00:32:08.680 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What a horrible story.

00:32:08.680 --> 00:32:10.230 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: It is a
horrible story, and there

00:32:10.230 --> 00:32:12.030 align:middle line:84%
is a theory that's
quite well regarded,

00:32:12.030 --> 00:32:14.160 align:middle line:84%
the man from the
train theory, which

00:32:14.160 --> 00:32:19.140 align:middle line:84%
posits that this was a hobo
riding the rails across the US.

00:32:19.140 --> 00:32:21.960 align:middle line:84%
And in those days, police
departments and jurisdictions

00:32:21.960 --> 00:32:23.130 align:middle line:90%
didn't talk to one another.

00:32:23.130 --> 00:32:23.250 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Right.

00:32:23.250 --> 00:32:24.390 align:middle line:90%
And they didn't have computers.

00:32:24.390 --> 00:32:25.190 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Right.

00:32:25.190 --> 00:32:26.610 align:middle line:84%
So the concept of
a serial killer

00:32:26.610 --> 00:32:28.590 align:middle line:90%
really wasn't well known then.

00:32:28.590 --> 00:32:31.110 align:middle line:84%
But there were a series of very
similar murders, all of them

00:32:31.110 --> 00:32:33.090 align:middle line:84%
very close to railroad
tracks, heading

00:32:33.090 --> 00:32:35.370 align:middle line:84%
across the US, and one of
them kind of local to us

00:32:35.370 --> 00:32:37.830 align:middle line:90%
here in Colorado Springs.

00:32:37.830 --> 00:32:40.350 align:middle line:84%
Always the family killed
with their own hatchet.

00:32:40.350 --> 00:32:42.660 align:middle line:84%
Always every reflective
surface-- windows,

00:32:42.660 --> 00:32:45.060 align:middle line:84%
mirrors inside the
house-- covered up.

00:32:45.060 --> 00:32:47.700 align:middle line:84%
Always an assault upon the
most attractive female member

00:32:47.700 --> 00:32:48.570 align:middle line:90%
of the house.

00:32:48.570 --> 00:32:51.687 align:middle line:84%
The parallels are
very well regarded.

00:32:51.687 --> 00:32:53.270 align:middle line:84%
But most of those
properties are gone.

00:32:53.270 --> 00:32:55.920 align:middle line:84%
Villisca, you can
still visit today,

00:32:55.920 --> 00:32:58.800 align:middle line:84%
and I spent several days
and nights researching that.

00:32:58.800 --> 00:33:02.400 align:middle line:84%
And there is something
about that house

00:33:02.400 --> 00:33:04.400 align:middle line:90%
that is not quite right.

00:33:04.400 --> 00:33:06.555 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Are you the
modern day Truman Capote?

00:33:06.555 --> 00:33:07.355 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:33:07.355 --> 00:33:08.800 align:middle line:84%
This sounds like
"In Cold Blood."

00:33:08.800 --> 00:33:10.370 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: I would
not be so arrogant

00:33:10.370 --> 00:33:13.090 align:middle line:84%
as to presume to be at
his standard of writing.

00:33:13.090 --> 00:33:17.170 align:middle line:84%
But I find that the story
of Villisca fascinates me.

00:33:17.170 --> 00:33:20.020 align:middle line:84%
You go to the cemetery
in town, and all eight

00:33:20.020 --> 00:33:22.270 align:middle line:90%
of those poor victims are--

00:33:22.270 --> 00:33:24.235 align:middle line:84%
their graves are in one
long, continuous plot.

00:33:24.235 --> 00:33:25.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That's
a horrible story.

00:33:25.610 --> 00:33:28.180 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Yeah, and nobody has
ever answered for that crime.

00:33:28.180 --> 00:33:29.772 align:middle line:84%
They did not catch
any perpetrator.

00:33:29.772 --> 00:33:31.480 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Would that
person still be alive

00:33:31.480 --> 00:33:32.200 align:middle line:90%
or they'd be dead by now?

00:33:32.200 --> 00:33:33.200 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Not right-- no.

00:33:33.200 --> 00:33:35.090 align:middle line:84%
No, they would not
be alive any longer.

00:33:35.090 --> 00:33:38.050 align:middle line:84%
This was back in
the early 1900s,

00:33:38.050 --> 00:33:39.260 align:middle line:90%
so they got away with it.

00:33:39.260 --> 00:33:41.170 align:middle line:84%
And there are many
theories about-- just as

00:33:41.170 --> 00:33:42.430 align:middle line:90%
with the Zodiac killings.

00:33:42.430 --> 00:33:44.980 align:middle line:84%
Zodiac could, I guess, be
in a nursing home right now.

00:33:44.980 --> 00:33:45.520 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He could be.

00:33:45.520 --> 00:33:46.320 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Yeah.

00:33:46.320 --> 00:33:48.220 align:middle line:84%
The Villisca murderer
is long dead and gone.

00:33:48.220 --> 00:33:49.030 align:middle line:90%
Or murderers.

00:33:49.030 --> 00:33:51.145 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Were there other
cases similar to that

00:33:51.145 --> 00:33:54.460 align:middle line:84%
that you might have been able to
tie together with that murder?

00:33:54.460 --> 00:33:55.990 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: With the
Villisca murders?

00:33:55.990 --> 00:33:58.030 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely, there were several.

00:33:58.030 --> 00:33:59.430 align:middle line:84%
And again, if you
plot them out--

00:33:59.430 --> 00:34:00.820 align:middle line:84%
there is a great
book I recommend

00:34:00.820 --> 00:34:02.500 align:middle line:84%
called "The Man From
the Train," which

00:34:02.500 --> 00:34:03.950 align:middle line:90%
lays all of this stuff out.

00:34:03.950 --> 00:34:06.120 align:middle line:84%
It was written by a
baseball statistician

00:34:06.120 --> 00:34:09.040 align:middle line:84%
of all things whose hobby
was looking at stats

00:34:09.040 --> 00:34:11.165 align:middle line:84%
and then realized, there's
a pattern here emerging.

00:34:11.165 --> 00:34:12.498 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: There's something here.

00:34:12.498 --> 00:34:14.469 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: These ax murders
spread across the US,

00:34:14.469 --> 00:34:16.280 align:middle line:90%
tracking railroad.

00:34:16.280 --> 00:34:17.080 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh.

00:34:17.080 --> 00:34:21.670 align:middle line:84%
So this hobo, as they would
call them, jumped on the train,

00:34:21.670 --> 00:34:25.570 align:middle line:84%
went to a city, did his heinous
deeds, jumped on a train

00:34:25.570 --> 00:34:28.056 align:middle line:84%
again, went to another city
and did it all over again.

00:34:28.056 --> 00:34:29.139 align:middle line:90%
And they never caught him.

00:34:29.139 --> 00:34:29.939 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Right.

00:34:29.939 --> 00:34:31.480 align:middle line:84%
And it scarred the
town of Villisca.

00:34:31.480 --> 00:34:35.409 align:middle line:84%
I mean, for the longest time,
people believed it was a local.

00:34:35.409 --> 00:34:38.143 align:middle line:84%
And so there were stories
of whole families--

00:34:38.143 --> 00:34:40.060 align:middle line:84%
so you would get together
with your neighbors,

00:34:40.060 --> 00:34:41.449 align:middle line:84%
because they feared
this would happen again.

00:34:41.449 --> 00:34:42.280 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I bet they
were petrified.

00:34:42.280 --> 00:34:43.080 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Right.

00:34:43.080 --> 00:34:44.920 align:middle line:84%
And so the fathers
would take it in turns

00:34:44.920 --> 00:34:46.715 align:middle line:84%
to sit up at night
with a shotgun.

00:34:46.715 --> 00:34:48.340 align:middle line:84%
You would have two
families in a house.

00:34:48.340 --> 00:34:50.962 align:middle line:84%
They would sleep in shifts,
two hours on, two hours off.

00:34:50.962 --> 00:34:53.170 align:middle line:84%
Dad would sit up with a
shotgun, waiting for somebody

00:34:53.170 --> 00:34:54.159 align:middle line:90%
to break in.

00:34:54.159 --> 00:34:55.690 align:middle line:84%
They never understood
that this was

00:34:55.690 --> 00:34:58.690 align:middle line:84%
a stranger that came in, struck
one night, and then moved on.

00:34:58.690 --> 00:35:00.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What's the
target date for this book?

00:35:00.730 --> 00:35:03.063 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: This book will be
out in November of this year.

00:35:03.063 --> 00:35:05.590 align:middle line:84%
I have one more visit to
pay to Villisca, which I'll

00:35:05.590 --> 00:35:07.540 align:middle line:90%
be doing at the end of July.

00:35:07.540 --> 00:35:09.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Does it feel
creepy when you're there?

00:35:09.670 --> 00:35:10.990 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: It absolutely does.

00:35:10.990 --> 00:35:13.720 align:middle line:84%
And I recorded the
last time I was there.

00:35:13.720 --> 00:35:16.480 align:middle line:84%
I was with two other
grown men in the house,

00:35:16.480 --> 00:35:19.220 align:middle line:84%
and we recorded the sound
of children laughing.

00:35:19.220 --> 00:35:20.020 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Laughing.

00:35:20.020 --> 00:35:20.550 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Laughing.

00:35:20.550 --> 00:35:21.250 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Not crying.

00:35:21.250 --> 00:35:22.050 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: No.

00:35:22.050 --> 00:35:23.923 align:middle line:90%
Giggling, laughing children.

00:35:23.923 --> 00:35:25.090 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That freaks me out.

00:35:25.090 --> 00:35:26.090 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Freaked me out.

00:35:26.090 --> 00:35:29.270 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Children sounds
of ghosts freak me out.

00:35:29.270 --> 00:35:30.410 align:middle line:90%
I don't know why.

00:35:30.410 --> 00:35:31.670 align:middle line:90%
They're kids.

00:35:31.670 --> 00:35:33.437 align:middle line:90%
But they just sound eerie.

00:35:33.437 --> 00:35:35.270 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Definitely, I
would agree with you.

00:35:35.270 --> 00:35:39.110 align:middle line:84%
And we had similar unusual
phenomena with flashlights.

00:35:39.110 --> 00:35:41.750 align:middle line:84%
Now, there is an old
technique with Maglites,

00:35:41.750 --> 00:35:43.820 align:middle line:84%
those magnetic flashlights
where you unscrew them

00:35:43.820 --> 00:35:45.170 align:middle line:90%
to a certain level.

00:35:45.170 --> 00:35:47.630 align:middle line:84%
That's been pretty
effectively debunked.

00:35:47.630 --> 00:35:50.330 align:middle line:84%
It's proven that as the current
passes through the flashlight,

00:35:50.330 --> 00:35:52.287 align:middle line:84%
it will expand and
contract, and therefore you

00:35:52.287 --> 00:35:53.120 align:middle line:90%
get that flickering.

00:35:53.120 --> 00:35:55.100 align:middle line:84%
So I don't put much
stock in Maglites,

00:35:55.100 --> 00:35:57.740 align:middle line:84%
but the electronic
LED flashlights,

00:35:57.740 --> 00:36:00.590 align:middle line:84%
which have an On/Off button,
we were getting those switching

00:36:00.590 --> 00:36:03.150 align:middle line:84%
themselves off and on in the
Villisca Ax Murder House,

00:36:03.150 --> 00:36:05.150 align:middle line:84%
and that's a whole different
level of phenomenon

00:36:05.150 --> 00:36:05.810 align:middle line:90%
that you can't explain.

00:36:05.810 --> 00:36:07.640 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What entity might
have been doing that?

00:36:07.640 --> 00:36:08.973 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Well, here's the thing.

00:36:08.973 --> 00:36:10.650 align:middle line:84%
The killer didn't
die in the house.

00:36:10.650 --> 00:36:12.020 align:middle line:84%
The only people that
died in the house--

00:36:12.020 --> 00:36:12.530 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's a good point--

00:36:12.530 --> 00:36:15.010 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Were the
innocents that lived there.

00:36:15.010 --> 00:36:18.250 align:middle line:84%
So a theory that I have,
one that we don't really

00:36:18.250 --> 00:36:21.740 align:middle line:84%
give too much thought to,
is paranormal enthusiasts

00:36:21.740 --> 00:36:25.060 align:middle line:84%
such as myself, people that go
to all of these locations, many

00:36:25.060 --> 00:36:26.630 align:middle line:90%
of them go to Villisca.

00:36:26.630 --> 00:36:30.190 align:middle line:84%
I think sometimes we take
along attachments with us.

00:36:30.190 --> 00:36:34.210 align:middle line:84%
I think in the same way that you
can dirt into somebody's house

00:36:34.210 --> 00:36:36.520 align:middle line:84%
if you go visit, you don't
wipe your feet properly--

00:36:36.520 --> 00:36:37.540 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You bring something in.

00:36:37.540 --> 00:36:37.970 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Yeah.

00:36:37.970 --> 00:36:39.790 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
much of this activity

00:36:39.790 --> 00:36:42.670 align:middle line:84%
may be unrelated to what
took place at the house.

00:36:42.670 --> 00:36:45.490 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There seems to be a lot
of sadness connected to it too.

00:36:45.490 --> 00:36:46.120 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: There is.

00:36:46.120 --> 00:36:48.250 align:middle line:84%
And sleeping in that house
is not a pleasant experience.

00:36:48.250 --> 00:36:49.333 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You've done that?

00:36:49.333 --> 00:36:50.500 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: I have.

00:36:50.500 --> 00:36:52.590 align:middle line:84%
If you go upstairs to
the master bedroom--

00:36:52.590 --> 00:36:55.300 align:middle line:84%
and it's an open plan bedroom
at the top of the stairs--

00:36:55.300 --> 00:36:57.640 align:middle line:84%
there are a series of
nicks on the ceiling.

00:36:57.640 --> 00:37:00.250 align:middle line:84%
And it takes a moment
before you realize that was

00:37:00.250 --> 00:37:02.420 align:middle line:90%
from the back swing of the ax.

00:37:02.420 --> 00:37:04.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And they kept
these things intact?

00:37:04.830 --> 00:37:06.580 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: It's in the
ceiling of the house.

00:37:06.580 --> 00:37:07.495 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:37:07.495 --> 00:37:08.763 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Fix the ceiling.

00:37:08.763 --> 00:37:10.930 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: But you know, then
you're changing history,

00:37:10.930 --> 00:37:13.890 align:middle line:84%
and I think there's a lot to be
said for preserving something

00:37:13.890 --> 00:37:15.265 align:middle line:84%
like this for
future generations.

00:37:15.265 --> 00:37:17.598 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And that's why they
have kept it the way it is.

00:37:17.598 --> 00:37:19.980 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: It's not the kind
of place you enjoy visiting,

00:37:19.980 --> 00:37:21.590 align:middle line:90%
but it has its lessons.

00:37:21.590 --> 00:37:22.560 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Small house?

00:37:22.560 --> 00:37:25.185 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Very, very small house.

00:37:25.185 --> 00:37:27.838 align:middle line:84%
I usually take two or no more
than three people with me

00:37:27.838 --> 00:37:29.130 align:middle line:90%
when I investigate in Villisca.

00:37:29.130 --> 00:37:33.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Do you think they let
him in, or did he break in?

00:37:33.120 --> 00:37:34.590 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Well, here's the thing.

00:37:34.590 --> 00:37:37.535 align:middle line:84%
One theory suggests that
he was hiding in the barn,

00:37:37.535 --> 00:37:39.660 align:middle line:84%
watching the family come
and go throughout the day.

00:37:39.660 --> 00:37:41.520 align:middle line:90%
Then they went to church.

00:37:41.520 --> 00:37:44.280 align:middle line:84%
So one theory says that he broke
in while they were at church,

00:37:44.280 --> 00:37:48.420 align:middle line:84%
waited in the attic, and then
came out when they were asleep.

00:37:48.420 --> 00:37:52.050 align:middle line:84%
Another says that he broke in
through a downstairs window,

00:37:52.050 --> 00:37:54.420 align:middle line:84%
taking their ax
from the woodpile

00:37:54.420 --> 00:37:55.860 align:middle line:90%
after they'd all gone to bed.

00:37:55.860 --> 00:37:59.007 align:middle line:84%
And a third theory says
that he had an accomplice.

00:37:59.007 --> 00:38:00.090 align:middle line:90%
But I will tell you this--

00:38:00.090 --> 00:38:01.632 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now if he
had an accomplice,

00:38:01.632 --> 00:38:03.570 align:middle line:84%
this person traveled
with him all the time.

00:38:03.570 --> 00:38:05.438 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Exactly.

00:38:05.438 --> 00:38:06.480 align:middle line:90%
But I will tell you this.

00:38:06.480 --> 00:38:08.670 align:middle line:84%
It's impossible to be
silent in that house.

00:38:08.670 --> 00:38:12.540 align:middle line:84%
Those old wooden balloon
frame buildings creak.

00:38:12.540 --> 00:38:14.470 align:middle line:84%
You cannot climb that
staircase quietly.

00:38:14.470 --> 00:38:15.270 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: No.

00:38:15.270 --> 00:38:17.490 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: So it's a
mystery to me how

00:38:17.490 --> 00:38:20.520 align:middle line:84%
he was able to do what
he did without waking

00:38:20.520 --> 00:38:22.640 align:middle line:90%
the whole family up.

00:38:22.640 --> 00:38:25.730 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And whatever he
did, he had to do fast.

00:38:25.730 --> 00:38:27.870 align:middle line:84%
The screams alone would
wake up the other ones

00:38:27.870 --> 00:38:28.670 align:middle line:90%
and they'd run out.

00:38:28.670 --> 00:38:30.920 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And then spent the
whole night in the house

00:38:30.920 --> 00:38:31.720 align:middle line:90%
afterwards.

00:38:31.720 --> 00:38:33.890 align:middle line:84%
So the best guess is the
killings occurred sometime

00:38:33.890 --> 00:38:36.560 align:middle line:84%
after midnight, and that he
left sometime before dawn.

00:38:36.560 --> 00:38:38.540 align:middle line:84%
So he was in the house
for several hours--

00:38:38.540 --> 00:38:39.460 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: With all
the dead bodies.

00:38:39.460 --> 00:38:41.085 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: --with all
of the dead bodies.

00:38:41.085 --> 00:38:43.020 align:middle line:90%
And even cooked himself food.

00:38:43.020 --> 00:38:43.820 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: No.

00:38:43.820 --> 00:38:45.180 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Mm-hmm.

00:38:45.180 --> 00:38:46.650 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Truly a sick person.

00:38:46.650 --> 00:38:48.090 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Absolutely.

00:38:48.090 --> 00:38:50.287 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What creates
someone like that?

00:38:50.287 --> 00:38:52.370 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: Well, this is the
great debate, isn't it?

00:38:52.370 --> 00:38:52.740 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:38:52.740 --> 00:38:54.657 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: It's the whole
nature versus nurture.

00:38:54.657 --> 00:38:57.400 align:middle line:84%
Are some people
just wired wrong?

00:38:57.400 --> 00:38:59.850 align:middle line:90%
Are some people just born evil?

00:38:59.850 --> 00:39:00.792 align:middle line:90%
Or is it a--

00:39:00.792 --> 00:39:02.250 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Something
happened to him.

00:39:02.250 --> 00:39:03.050 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Yeah.

00:39:03.050 --> 00:39:05.490 align:middle line:84%
Or is there an event
that happens which twists

00:39:05.490 --> 00:39:06.770 align:middle line:90%
somebody, that corrupts them?

00:39:06.770 --> 00:39:08.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Abused as a child
or something horrible.

00:39:08.980 --> 00:39:10.980 align:middle line:84%
>>ESTEP: And I researched
so many serial killers

00:39:10.980 --> 00:39:12.160 align:middle line:90%
for this book.

00:39:12.160 --> 00:39:14.640 align:middle line:84%
There are many defining
characteristics in childhood

00:39:14.640 --> 00:39:16.345 align:middle line:90%
that they have in common.

00:39:16.345 --> 00:39:18.720 align:middle line:84%
A lot of them-- the male serial
killers-- because they're

00:39:18.720 --> 00:39:19.780 align:middle line:90%
predominantly male.

00:39:19.780 --> 00:39:20.580 align:middle line:90%
There are few--

00:39:20.580 --> 00:39:21.110 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Most are.

00:39:21.110 --> 00:39:21.910 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Yeah.

00:39:21.910 --> 00:39:24.030 align:middle line:84%
There are a few, but some
female serial killers.

00:39:24.030 --> 00:39:26.920 align:middle line:84%
But many of them are
mommy's boys, you know?

00:39:26.920 --> 00:39:27.720 align:middle line:90%
They were--

00:39:27.720 --> 00:39:28.800 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Like Ted Bundy.

00:39:28.800 --> 00:39:30.360 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Yeah, absolutely.

00:39:30.360 --> 00:39:35.790 align:middle line:84%
They were doted upon by their
mothers to an unusual degree.

00:39:35.790 --> 00:39:36.780 align:middle line:90%
So there is that.

00:39:36.780 --> 00:39:40.290 align:middle line:84%
Early incidences of bedwetting
that go on late into childhood

00:39:40.290 --> 00:39:42.240 align:middle line:90%
and sometimes adulthood.

00:39:42.240 --> 00:39:44.520 align:middle line:84%
But also a fundamental
lack of empathy, and I

00:39:44.520 --> 00:39:46.830 align:middle line:84%
think that's to me the
defining characteristic.

00:39:46.830 --> 00:39:52.100 align:middle line:84%
To do what they do, you cannot
regard your victim as a person.

00:39:52.100 --> 00:39:53.493 align:middle line:90%
They dehumanize people.

00:39:53.493 --> 00:39:54.410 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They have to.

00:39:54.410 --> 00:39:54.800 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Yeah.

00:39:54.800 --> 00:39:56.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It's the only way
for them to do what they do.

00:39:56.720 --> 00:39:57.520 align:middle line:90%
>>ESTEP: Yeah.

00:39:57.520 --> 00:40:00.200 align:middle line:84%
The way you and I might
carve up our lunch,

00:40:00.200 --> 00:40:01.190 align:middle line:90%
